Commentary: Philander starts with a good length ball around off, Crawley comes forward and blocks it off the front foot.
This time Vernon bowls it in the channel outside off, Crawley makes a leave.
Beauty! Brilliant line and length from Philander. He pitches this one around off and makes it move away just a hint. Crawley pokes to get beaten.

Follows it with another ripper! Pitches this one around off on a good length. Crawley has to play at it. He comes forward and looks to defend but a hint of movement is enough to beat the outside edge.
This time Philander strays on the pads of Crawley. He easily works it behind square leg for a single to get the scoreboard ticking.
Landed around off on a length, it is defended. A tight over from Philander. Always on the money is the Big Vern and nothing different here either from him.

Rabada is on the money straightaway too! A good length ball around off from him. Unlike Philander, Rabada makes it come into the right-hander. Crawley looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Fullish ball outside off, some late swing on it too. Crawley looks to reach out and drive but pulls his bat away at the last moment.
Fuller again, this time just outside off, Crawley leans into the shot and drives it through covers. Before Maharaj can get to the ball with a slide, the batters take three.
FOUR! Off the mark nicely! Not a very good ball from Rabada as he bowls it full and too straight. Sibley easily flicks it to the deep mid-wicket fence. First boundary of the innings.
Fuller ball just outside off, late swing on it too. Sibley looks to dig it out but gets beaten.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Beaten! Brilliant from Philander. Another ball around off on a good length. It once again moves away from the forward defensive poke of Crawley.
Landed fullish around off, Crawley keeps it out.
Good length ball around off again, blocked onto the pitch by Zak.
Slightly fuller and around off, Crawley takes a good stride forward and blocks it out nicely.

OUT! Caught Behind! Brilliant from de Kock behind the wicket. Superb from Philander too. Continues bowling on the fourth stump channel on a good length. It swings away a bit. Crawley looks to defend off the front foot but the ball takes the outside edge and goes behind. De Kock dives to his right nicely and pouches it in his mitts. Top start for the Proteas. Not so good for England and Crawley.
Slightly fuller around off, asking the batter to drive but Sibley is not lured into the shot as he makes a leave.
EDGY FOUR! Length ball around off, Sibley looks to work it on the leg side but the ball takes the thickish outside edge and goes between third slip and gully. It races to the third man fence.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length ball around middle, tucked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fullish and outside off again, Denly lets it be.
Just short! Slightly fuller and outside off, Denly pokes at the ball with hard hands. The ball takes the outer half of the bat and goes to the gully fielder on the bounce.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley defends it off the back foot to the leg side.
On a length on off, Dominic stands tall and defends it to point.
On off, Sibley plays it with soft hands and guides it to gully. The fielder there slides and makes the stop.
Fullish outside off, left alone by Sibley.
Just ahead of a good length area, Sibley comes forward to defend but the ball takes the thick outside edge and goes to second slip but on the bounce.
Good leave! A good length ball that lands outside off, it comes back in nicely but Sibley has his timbers covered as he lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish length ball outside off, Denly has no problems in shouldering his arms.
Fuller ball on off, Denly keeps it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Landed around off, Denly comes forward and pushes it to mid off.
In the channel outside off, Denly makes another leave.
Driven well but straight to the point fielder. So, Denly will remain on nought. A fuller ball outside off, Joe reaches out and creams the drive but straight to the fielder.
FOUR! Whipped away! A gift on the pads from Philander. Overpitched on the pads, Sibley flicks it brilliantly and it races to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Shortish length ball around off, Sibley rides the bounce and taps it towards covers.
Ripper! Absolute ripper! Good length ball around off, Sibley comes forward to defend but the ball moves away from his bat and goes behind. Lucky not to edge that one.

Follows it with another beauty. He can just keep landing the ball on the same spot and keep bothering the batters. That's what he is doing with Sibley. Pitches it slightly closer to the off pole on a good length and makes it move away from the defensive poke of Sibley.

Now this one comes back in. Good length ball around off, it comes into Sibley sharply as he looks to defend it off the back foot. Sibley looks to defend but it seems like the ball took the inside edge and went onto the pads.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Good length around off, Denly pushes it towards cover by getting behind the line of the ball.
Another one which is on a good length around off, Denly blocks it out.
FOUR! Denly is off the mark in good fashion. A good length ball outside off, Denly reaches out and drives it through point to get his first boundary of the innings.
Outside off, Denly this time covers his stumps and lets it be.
Punched nicely! A fuller ball around off, Denly this time punches it through point. The ball is racing towards the fence but Malan from gully chases it down and keeps the batters to two.
In the channel outside off from Rabada, Denly makes a leave now.
Full delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Beautiful shot from Sibley. This will give him a lot of confidence. Fullish on off, Sibley leans forward and creams the drive through extra cover for a boundary.
On middle, Dominic defends it off the back foot.
Fullish delivery outside off, Sibley does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.

BEATEN! Lovely delivery from Philander! Good length delivery around off nipping away from the batsman, Sibley looks to defend it but misses altogether. Philander seems interested for caught behind but the umpire shakes his head. Faf du Plessis is not interested for the review.
Good length ball outisde off, Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
On a length on off, Denly looks to defend it but it goes off the inner half of the bat towards square leg. A single taken.
Back of a length ball outside off, Sibley makes a leave to the keeper.
Good length on middle, Dominic blocks it to square leg.
Full on middle, Dominic works it to mid-wicket.
Fullish outside off, Sibley lets the ball through to the keeper.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Sibley ducks under it.
Good length delivery on middle but it bounces extra, Denly looks to defend it but it hits the handle of the bat and goes towards the leg side. No run.
On a length outside off shaping away, Joe looks to defend it but fails to get any bat on it. Brilliant bowling from Philander.
Fullish on off, Denly taps it to point.

FOUR! Hammered away! Short of a length on middle, Denly gets into position quickly and pulls it to the deep square leg region for a boundary. The fielder from fine leg gives it a chase  but fails to cut it off.
On a length on off, Joe defends it off the back foot.
Short of a length on middle and leg, Joe ducks under it.
Fullish outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length ball outside off, Sibley sways away from it.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and off, Dominic does well to evade it.
Good length delivery outside off, Sibley lets the ball go to the keeper.
On the pads, Sibley flicks it to deep square leg and picks up a single.
Outside off, left alone by Denly.
Nortje starts with a fullish delivery on off, Sibley blocks it to point.
On middle, Dominic plays it back to the bowler.
Full one on off, Sibley moves to the off side and defends it to mid on.
Length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Fullish delivery on off, Sibley takes a stride forward and drives it through covers. The fielders from mid off and cover hare after it. The former slides and cleans it up. Two taken.
On a length outside off, Sibley lets the ball go to the keeper.
Starts with a flighted ball on off, Denly pushes it to cover.
On off, Denly drives it to long off and picks up a single.
Floated on middle and leg, Sibley works it to mid-wicket.
OHH! Looped up ball on middle, Sibley comes down the track and looks to push it to the leg side but gets a thick outside edge. It rolls towards point.
FOUR! Poor bowling! Full delivery down the leg side, Sibley will not miss out on these as he just flicks it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Tossed up ball on middle, Sibley defends it back to the bowler off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Denly whips it wide of mid on for a single.
Good length ball on off, Sibley defends it to point.
Fullish delivery on middle, Dominic plays it back to the bowler.
On off, Sibley blocks it out onto the pitch.
Fullish outside off at 143 kph, Sibley lets it through to the keeper.
Length ball on off, Sibley stands tall and defends it out to cover.
Loopy delivery outside off, Denly pushes it to cover.
Floated on middle, Denly defends it back.
Outside off, pushed to cover.
Loopy delivery on off, Denly drives it to cover.
Flatter delivery outside off, Denly punches it to the cover fielder.
On off, pushed down to long off and a single is taken.
Full delivery on middle, Joe blocks it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Denly defends it solidly to cover.
FOUR! Errs in line does Nortje here and Denly makes full use of it. Short of a length down the leg side, Denly just helps it on its way to the fine leg fence.
Length ball on the fourth stump line, Denly makes a good leave to the keeper.
Shortish around off, Denly blocks it off the back foot.
Back of a length on off, Denly punches it to cover.
Starts with a full delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
On a length on off, Sibley rocks on his back foot and punches it to cover.
Length on off, Dominic taps it to the slip cordon.
Fullish delivery on middle, Sibley goes on his front foot and defends it solidly back to the bowler.
Sibley defends it solidly back to Pretorius.
On off, Sibley blocks it to cover.
Fullish on off, Denly blocks it to mid off.
Length on off, Denly rocks on his back foot and defends it off the back foot and onto the pitch.
BOUNCER! Bowled around middle and leg, Joe ducks under it.
Fullish on middle, Joe solidly plays it back to Nortje.
Short on middle, Denly pulls it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
On middle, Sibley pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller one on off, Denly takes a stride forward and defends it to cover.
Good length delivery on middle angling in, Denly looks to work it to the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls to square leg.
On middle, Denly flicks it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished! Full one on middle and leg, Sibley flicks it beautifully through mid-wicket for a boundary. 50 up for the visitors.
Length ball on middle, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length on middle, Denly works it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
On a length on off, Sibley blocks it to point.
On middle, Dominic defends it to cover.
On middle, Dominic defends it to cover.
FOUR BYES! Goes way over Sibley's head! Nortje bowls a bouncer around middle and leg, Sibley ducks under it. Quinton jumps in an attempt to pouch it but it goes over and into the fence for four byes.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Sibley works it to leg gully.
Fuller delivery on off, Denly defends it to the bowler.
On middle, Denly is solid in his defense and does so towards mid on.
Good length on off, Denly looks to defend it but it goes off the bottom edge and onto the pads.
Good length on middle, Denly whips it to mid-wicket.
Short on off, Denly punches it to cover.
Fuller one on middle, defended back to Pretorius.
Fullish outside off, Sibley shoulders arms.

EDGY FOUR! Sibley has been leaving those well but goes after this one. Good length delivery outside off, Sibley pokes at it with hard hands but gets an outside edge which goes between the second slip and the gully fielder. The ball races to the third man fence quickly. The boundary brings up the 50-run stand between the two.
Length ball outside off, Sibley lets this one through to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone by Sibley.
BEATEN! Ripper from Rabada! Dishes out a length ball around off, moving away. Sibley attempts to defend it but fails to get anything.
On a length on off, Dominic camps back and defends it out.
On off, Denly blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Denly tucks it to mid-wicket.
Fullish delivery on off, Joe drives it but finds the mid off fielder.
Fuller one on middle, Denly blocks it out onto the pitch.
Another one which is full on middle, Joe pushes it to mid on.
On off, Denly lunges forward and defends it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley lets the ball go to the keeper.
Nicely played! Fullish on off, Sibley strides forward and drives it through mid off and picks up a couple before the fielder can clean it up.
Back of a length ball on middle, Sibley stands tall and plays it back to Rabada.
BEATEN! Beautiful delivery! Back of a length ball outside off, Sibley looks to defend it but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! Outstanding from Rabada and the patience of bowling in the channel outside off pays rich dividends. Good length ball, shaping away a bit. Sibley looks to defend off the back foot but it hits the outside edge and goes towards first slip. Quinton de Kock dives to his right and pouches it safely. Sibley could have left that one alone. The hosts have struck just before Lunch and the budding stand has been cut short.
Full on middle, Root defends it out to mid on.
On middle, Denly defends it back to the bowler.
On a length on off, Denly looks to defend it but gets an outside edge which goes to cover. No run.
Length ball on off, Denly pushes it to cover.
Good length on middle, Denly works it to mid-wicket.
Fuller one on off, Denly strides forward and solidly blocks it to cover.
Good length outside off, Denly leaves it alone. Quinton  fails to collect it cleanly. The ball rolls to the off side.
Back of a length ball on middle, Root looks to duck under but it does not bounce as much and hits him around the chest. Luckily, for Root there is no damage done.
BEATEN! Nicely bowled! Good length ball on off, Root attempts to defend it off the back foot but the ball whizzes past the bat and into the mitts of the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Root works it to mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, Root plays it to the leg side.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Back of a length on off, Root stands tall and punches it through the point region for a boundary.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Floated ball on middle, Denly whips it to mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery on off, Denly plays it back to the bowler off the front foot.
On off, pushed to point.
Loopy delivery on middle, Denly defends it to Maharaj.
Flatter delivery on middle, JD works it to the leg side.

BEATEN! First signs of some spin from Maharaj on this wicket. Beautiful bowling though from the left-arm spinner though. Tosses this one up on off, spinning away. Denly goes on his front foot and looks to defend it. He misses it altogether. Brilliant ball to end the session. With that it is LUNCH ON DAY 1.
Philander starts with a good length ball around off, Root taps it towards point.
Shortish this time and once again around off, Root goes on the back foot and defends.
In the channel outside off this time, Root covers his stumps and lets it be.
Landed around off on a good length, pushed to covers.
Shortish ball outside off, Root taps it towards point where the fielder misfields and allows a single.
Beauty to end the over! Back of a length ball just outside off, Denly hops and then pokes at the ball. It moves away sharply to beat the outside edge.
Maharaj starts the spell by a flighted fuller ball around off, Root defends it out.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Cut away! Shortish ball just outside off, Root goes on the back foot and cuts it through point. Rabada gives it a chase, slides to pull the ball back but in vain.
Outside off, driven to covers.
Flatter one around off again, Root taps it through cover-point for a single.
Lands this one around off and makes it turn further away. Denly allows it to go to the keeper.
FOUR! Punched nicely! A good length ball outside off, Root goes back and punches it to the deep point fence.
Shortish ball outside off, Root this time taps it to third man for a single.
Landed around off, it is defended towards cover.
Good length ball around off, Denly blocks it right under his eyes.
Shortish ball on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, pushed to mid on.
Flatter ball just outside off, Root pushes it to covers.
On off, driven back to the bowler.
Shortish ball outside off, tapped towards covers.
Fuller ball outside off, Root goes for the sweep but does not connect it well. It goes towards square leg off the inner half of the bat for a single.
Flatter one outside off, it is kept out.
Flighted fuller ball around off, Denly comes forward and blocks it.
Shortish ball just outside off, tapped towards point.
Good length ball on off, Root looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes behind square on the leg side. A single taken.
Slightly short around off, Denly tucks it to mid-wicket.
Beaten! Nicely bowled! Good length ball outside off, Denly is drawn into the shot as he comes forward and looks to drive. The ball shapes away to beat the outside edge.
This time he gets right behind the line of the ball and defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, pushed to mid on.
Fuller ball around off, Root drives it through cover. Nortje from there does well to save runs for his side. Just a single.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy ball around off, defended.
Slower through the air around off, it is defended.
Floated ball around off, Denly comes down the track and looks to defend but goes off the pads towards point. Maharaj appeals but the umpire shakes his head.
Fuller ball outside off, Denly drives it well but straight to covers.
Good length ball around middle, worked towards square leg.
Fuller ball just outside off, Root drills it nicely but cannot beat Elgar at cover.
Length ball on off, Root pushes it towards point for an easy run.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
In the corridor of uncertainty. Denly lets it be.
Fuller around off, driven straight to mid off.
Loopy ball on off, Root eases a single through mid off.
On middle, pushed to mid on.
On off, pushed towards mid off.
Shortish ball outside off, Denly looks to cut but ends up bottom edging it towards point.
Quicker one outside off, Denly stays on the back foot and pushes it towards point.
FOUR! Finally runs, four of them for Denly. Maharaj bowls it short and outside off, Denly rocks on the back foot and slaps it through covers for a boundary. Runs after 48 balls.
Nortje starts with a full ball on middle, Root works it towards deep square leg. Before the fine leg fielder can get to the ball, a couple of runs for Root.
Outside off, an easy leave for the English captain.
Good length ball around off, Root blocks it back to the bowler.
Good running! Fuller ball around off and middle, Root uses his wrists and works it to deep mid-wicket. Before the fielder can get to the ball, Root takes three.
Another couple! Good aggressive running from Denly and Root. Another good length ball on middle, Denly works it nicely between fine leg and deep square leg. A couple more.
Bouncer down the leg side. Denly ducks under it. De Kock does well to move to his left and pouch the ball.
Flighted fuller ball around off, Root drives it straight to the cover fielder.
On middle, it is defended.
Quicker one on the pads, Root works it towards mid-wicket and thinks of a single but seeing the fielder getting to the ball quickly, he decides against it.
FOUR! Swept nicely! A fuller ball outside off, Root gets in the position and sweeps it brilliantly to the deep mid-wicket fence.
On middle, it is blocked.
In the air... but safe. Another fuller ball outside off, Root looks to sweep again but this time he gets a top edge. However, it drops in no man's land just ahead of fine leg. A single taken.
Good length ball around off, it is blocked off the back foot.
Good length ball just outside off, it is defended.
100 up for England. Good length ball around off again, Root easily taps it towards third man for a single.
Shortish ball on the body, Denly looks to pull but the ball hits the gloves and goes to de Kock on the bounce.

Ouch! On the helmet this time. Nortje bangs this one around off and it comes back in. Denly looks to duck under it but he is late in doing so. The ball hits the helmet and goes towards mid-wicket. They cross for a leg bye and we will have the mandatory concussion test now. Looked alright while crossing for the leg bye.
Good length ball around off, it is defended off the front foot by Root.
Floated on off, Denly blocks it out.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery on middle, Denly defends it solidly.
Full delivery on middle, Denly works it to mid on.
On middle, Denly blocks it out.
Slower through the air and on middle, Denly looks to work it on the leg side but ends up getting a soft leading edge which goes towards the off side.
Good length ball around off, it is defended.
Another length ball on off, Root keeps it out.

FOUR! Dropped! Oh dear! How costly will this be. Slightly fullish ball from Nortje. Root is lured into the drive. No feet movement from him as he drives away from his body. The ball takes the thick outside edge and goes to van der Dussen at first slip quickly. De Kock dives to his right to catch but it is far from his reach. Dussen then looks to latch onto it  by moving to his left but he cannot hold on it. It races to the fence behind him.
Around off, blocked towards mid off.

OUT! Caught! The drop costs South Africa nothing as Nortje has bounced out the English skipper with a brilliant bouncer. Brilliant from Nortje. 148 kph bumper on middle, Root looks to duck under it but he is quite late in doing so. He ends up lobbing the ball towards de Kock. De Koock pouches it easily. The bowler appeals but de Kock is not very sure. The umpire signals nothing but Root walks off. Rassie and de Kock will be the relieved men. South Africa break another good-looking stand to dent the English progress. The replays roll in and show that the ball hit the gloves of Root.
Good length ball around off, Stokes keeps it out.
Floated ball on off, Denly defends it out.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Joe works it to the leg side.
BEATEN! Flatter delivery outisde off, Denly goes on his back foot to cut but misses it altogether.
FOUR! Poor ball this from Keshav Maharaj! Drifts this one down the leg side, Denly nudges it down to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On middle, Denly works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Stokes defends it out of the back foot.
Short delivery on middle, Ben Stokes pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length on off, Denly defends it to point.
BOUNCER! Bowled around middle, Denly ducks under it.
Fullish delivery on off, Joe pushes it back to the bowler.
Fullish delivery outside off, Denly lets the ball go to the keeper.
Floated ball on off, Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Stokes works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter delivery on middle, Ben tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Floated on off, Denly pushes it to cover.
On off, Denly lunges and blocks it out.
Flatter delivery outside off, Joe lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish on middle, Ben whips it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
On off, pushed back to Nortje off the front foot.
Short delivery on off, Denly pulls it comfortably to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
On a length on middle, Stokes goes on his back foot and blocks it to mid on.

FOUR! Nicely played but Philander cannot get to it. Full delivery on off, Stokes strokes it through mid off. Philander tries to come across and slides to get a hand on it. The ball goes through and into the long off fence. First one for Stokes in this innings.
Good length ball on middle, Ben defends it out of the back foot to the off side and crosses over for a single.
Floated one on middle, Stokes comes down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Loopy on off, Joe pushes it to cover.
Tossed up on middle, Joe flicks it to mid-wicket.
On off, flicked to mid-wicket.
Looped up ball on off, Denly pushes it to cover.
Floated one on middle, Joe plays it to mid on and takes a quick single to keep strike for the next over.
Good length ball on middle, Joe works it wide of mid on and takes a single.
Short of a length delivery on middle at 91 mph. Stokes looks to pull it but misses to get hit on the elbow. No harm done though.
Nortje bowls another short one but this one is down the leg side. Stokes just helps it on its way to fine leg. A single taken.
Fullish on middle, Denly whips it to deep mid-wicket and before the fielder can come across and clean it up, the batters pick up a couple.
Short of a length delivery on middle, Joe pulls it to deep mid-wicket and crosses over for a single.
Fullish on middle, Ben tucks it to mid-wicket for nothing.
Fullish delivery on off, Denly drives it to long off and takes a single.
Flat one on middle, Stokes works it to deep square leg and gives Denly the strike.

OUT! TIMBER! Right trhough the gate! What a delivery to get rid of the set batsman! Maharaj now gets into the wickets column. Arm ball on off, Denly strides forward to defend but the ball sneaks between the bat and pad going onto hitting the off stump. He trudges off after a long vigil out in the middle. A good knock from him but he should've had kept it out.
Loopy ball on off, Pope defends it off the front foot.
On off, Ollie defends it out.
Flatter one on middle, Pope pushes it back to Maharaj.
Starts with a full delivery on off, Stokes flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Stokes hops and defends it to point.
Good length ball outside off, Ben shoulders arms to it.
Fullish on off, Stokes pushes it to mid off.
On off, Stokes lunges forward and pushes it to mid off.
Back of a length ball on off, Stokes defends it out to the off side.
Full delivery on middle, Pope pushes it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery on middle, Ollie blocks it out.
Flatter delivery outside off, Pope cuts it to point.
Loopy delivery on middle and leg, Pope works it to square leg.
On off, Pope lunges forward and defends it out.
Tossed up ball on middle, Ollie defends it out to the bowler.
Fuller one on off, Ben pushes it to mid off.
BEATEN! Short of a length delivery outside off, Stokes pokes at it but misses it.
On middle, Stokes pushes it back to KR.
FOUR! Pulled away with disdain! Short delivery on middle, Stokes hammers the pull through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length outside off, Ben leaves it alone.
On middle, Stokes plays it back to the bowler.
Floated on middle, Pope blocks it onto the pitch.
Loopy on middle, Pope comes down the track and works it wide of mid on. Philander chases after it from mid off and cleans it up but cannot stop the batters from taking three. Pope is off the mark.
Flatter one on middle, Stokes pushes it back to the bowler but does so uppishly. It lands just short of Maharaj.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On middle, Ben works it to the leg side.
Loopy delivery on middle, Stokes pushes it down to long on for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Stokes works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Lovely from Stokes! Fullish delivery on off, Stokes creams the drive through the covers to pick up another boundary.
On a length outside off, Stokes lets the ball through to the keeper.
Rabada bowls a short one on middle, Stokes pulls it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
Back of a length delivery on off, Pope guides it towards third man. Pope hares after it and cleans it up. Two taken.
Fullish outside off, Ollie leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes works it to deep square leg and takes a single.
Good length on middle, Pope works it to mid-wicket.
On off, pushed back to Pretorius.
Fullish on middle, Pope plays it to the bowler.
Full one on off, Pope defends it solidly.
Good length ball on middle, Pope flicks it to mid-wicket.
On off, pushed to mid off by Stokes.
Good length ball on middle, Ben defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball on middle and leg, Stokes stands tall and works it to mid-wicket.
Fullish outside off, Stokes makes a leave to the keeper.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Ben blocks it out solidly.
Rabada dishes out another good length on off, Stokes taps it to gully.
Full delivery outside off, OP leaves it alone.
Full one on middle, Pope works it to short mid-wicket.
On off, Pope is solid in defense and does so towards cover.
Fullish one on off, Pope lunges forward and blocks it out.
Good length ball on middle, Ollie works it towards one of the short mid-wicket fielders.
Dwaine dishes a full ball on off, Pope drives it straight to the mid off fielder.
Fuller one outside off, Stokes blocks it to cover.
On a length on middle, Ben defends it off the back foot to mid-wicket.
Short of a length ball on middle, Stokes pulls it behind square and picks up a couple before the fielder can come across and clean it up.

EDGY FOUR! Ooohhh... almost another wicket. Very rare from Stokes. He is a positive player, so he either goes hard at the balls or lets them go. Very rarely do we see him so indecisive about shot-making. This was one of those moments. A length ball outside off, Ben is in two minds, whether to play at that or let it go. In the end, he does try that run-down-to-third-man shot but is late and gets a thick outside edge. Luckily for him, it goes between second slip and gully and the ball races to the third man fence. Nasser Hussain on air calls it a 'One-Day shot'. We have seen Joe Root play that shot so often in every format and even today, he was cross with himself for getting out. The reason - you can leave balls pitched outside off. Rabada will be frustrated a touch that did not go to hand but he will also be happy that he is causing some doubts in Stokesy's mind.
Good length ball on middle, Stokes blocks it out.
On a length on off, Stokes defends it out onto the pitch and says no for a single. TEA ON DAY 1.
Maharaj starts with a floated ball on middle, Pope works it to mid-wicket.
Looped up ball on middle, Ollie defends it back to Maharaj.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Pope works it to square leg. If he had missed, might have been out LBW.
On off, Ollie pushes it to cover.
Flat one on middle, Pope flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Full delivery on off, Stokes drives it back to the bowler who collects it on the bounce.
Full one outside off, Pope lets the ball go to the keeper.

BEATEN! Beautiful piece of bowling from Philander. Bowls it on back of a length, probably hitting a crack on the pitch and deviates away. Pope looks to defend it off the back foot but seems to have missed it completely. There is a mild appeal for caught behind but nothing from the umpire. Ultra Edge confirms there is no spike when the ball goes past the bat.
FOUR! Lovely. Fullish delivery on off, Pope lunges forward and creams the drive through extra covers for a boundary. First one for Pope.
On a length on off, Ollie defends it out.
Fullish delivery on off, Pope drives this through covers and picks up a couple. Malan hares after it and cleans it up.
On a length on off, Pope looks to defend it but it goes off the outside edge through gully. Malan chases it and slides to make the stop. Two taken.
Loopy delivery on off, Stokes comes down the track and blocks it out.
Flatter delivery on middle, Ben works it to the leg side.
Full on middle, Stokes flicks it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
On middle, Ollie dances down and flicks it to the leg side for a single.
Floated ball on middle, Stokes pushes it down to long on and crosses over for a single.
Tossed up ball outside off, Pope pushes it to cover.
Philander dishes a full one on off, Stokes defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Stokes takes a few steps forward and then blocks it out off the back foot.
On a length on middle and leg, Stokes works it to deep square leg and picks up another run.
FOUR! Errs in line does Philander and Pope does not miss out. Full delivery on the pads, Pope flicks it beautifully through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Good length on off, Ollie solidly defends it out.
Back of a length in the channel, Pope punches it to point off the back foot.
Flatter one on middle, Stokes works it to the leg side.
Another flat one with some spin, Stokes works it to square leg.
On middle, Stokes comes down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery on middle, Ben dances down and pushes it to mid on.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
On middle and leg, worked to square leg where the fielder makes a good sliding stop.
Fuller one on middle, Pope defends it solidly off the front foot.
Fuller one outside off, Ollie lets the ball go to the keeper.
On off, Pope lunges forward and blocks it to cover.
Good length on off, Pope taps it to point.
Vernon bowls another one which is full outside off, Pope solidly pushes it to point.
On off, driven to mid off.
Short of a length on middle, Stokes pulls it to square leg. The fielder fails to collect it cleanly but no run.
Flatter one on middle, Ben defends it out.
Flat on middle and leg, Ben blocks it,
On middle, Stokes tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full on middle, Ben pushes it to mid on.
SIX! Finally we see a maximum in this game! Maharaj tosses this one up on middle, Stokes puts on his dancing shoes and hammers it over the long on region for half a dozen.
Nortje starts with a fuller one outside off, Ollie does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.

SAFE! Almost did the trick! Short of a length on middle, Pope is late on his pull but gets a top edge but luckily for him it just goes over Vernon Philander at mid off. Before he can clean it up the batters take a single.
On a length on off, Stokes defends it out.
Where has that come from? Back of a length ball around off which bounces a little more than what Stokes expected. He looks to defend but gets hit on the gloves. Very well bowled from Nortje.

FOUR! Smashed! Back of a length ball outside off, Stokes stands tall and punches it through the covers for a boundary. 50-run stand is up between the two. England needed it after losing two quick wickets.
On middle, Stokes works it to deep square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! A poor ball and Stokes makes full use of it. Not a length to bowl to a batsman like Stokes. Short of a length on middle, Stokes camps back and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
On middle, Ben defends it back to Maharaj.
On middle, Stokes flicks it to the leg side for a single.

NOT OUT! Umpire's call it is on hitting the stumps. It is not a bad decision to review in the end as it looked very close. Maharaj floats this one up on middle and leg, Pope looks to defend it but gets hit flush on the pads. Maharaj appeals but the umpire shakes his head. Maharaj is confident and convinces Faf to go for the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there was no bat on it. The Ball Tracker is up now and it is umpire's call on hitting the leg stump. The Proteas do not lose a review.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
On middle, pushed towards mid on.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid on for a very quick single.
Full and around off, Stokes walks forward and pushes it back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT AT COVER! Gosh, gosh, gosh. Both sides would be thinking about that word. Just when England seemed well on top, right from nowhere, a wicket has fallen. And it is the man who scored a double century the first time he batted here in Tests. Ben Stokes looks at the ground crestfallen. He takes half a minute or so and then trudges off. This is a big boost for the Proteas. Full and outside off, Stokes looks to drive but his bottom hand comes off the bat. As a result, he is not in control of the shot and the ball flies off the face of the bat, straight to Dean Elgar at short cover. This did not hit a divot. This did not deviate off the seam. This did not swing in the air. Like many unexplained things in the universe, this just happened. Perhaps, when you are facing a bloke bowling close to 90 miles an hour, you sometimes do not have control of your shots. This was one of those times. This is what pace brings to Test cricket.
Streaky start. Full and around off, Buttler looks to work it to the leg side but the ball moves away slightly and goes off the leading edge through the covers. A single taken.
A bouncer now, Pope ducks.
Around off, solidly defended back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery on middle, Buttler works it wide of mid on and takes a single.
On off, Pope lunges forward and defends it out.
Flat one on middle and leg, Ollie pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller one outside off, Pope drives it to cover for nothing.
Tossed up ball on middle, Pope comes down the pitch and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery around off, Ollie takes a stride forward and pushes it to point.

FOUR! That will give Buttler some confidence. He has been out of touch for some while now. On a length outside off, Buttler camps back and punches it off the back foot through covers for a boundary. Two fielders chase after it but the ball wins the race.
Full on off, Jos defends it out to Nortje.

FOUR! But Buttler was lucky there. If he had missed, it would have been crashing into the stumps. Nortje bowls a full delivery on middle, Buttler moves to the off side and manages to get bat on it and flicks it to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Short of a length around off, Buttler looks to pull at first but then gets his bat out in time. Lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Jos defends it out.
Good length ball on off, Buttler taps it to point and calls Pope for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Pope was in though.

FOUR! Clever shot but risky as well. Floated ball on middle, Buttler plays the paddle sweep to fine leg. Vernon Philander hares after it and slides to make a stop. The umpires go in to check whether it is a four. The replays confirm that Philander has touched the ropes while trying to push the ball away.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On off, defended off the back foot to cover.
Flatter delivery on middle, Jos defends it out.

Was that a drop catch? From the reactions it certainly does look like it. Floated on off, Buttler drives it uppishly to silly mid off. It goes in between the legs of  him and through mid off. A single taken. The replays show that it might have burst through his hands but even if it was, it was a tough one.
Played to the mid-wicket region by the batsman. One run added to the total.
Full on middle, Pope defends it out.
Good length on middle, Ollie solidly blocks it.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and leg, Pope ducks under it.
Short of a length on middle, Pope has no problems in ducking under it.

Just short! Full delivery on off, Pope looks to drive it but gets a thick outside edge which goes towards second slip. The fielder comes forward in an attempt to catch but it falls short. Luck favouring Pope out there.
On a length outside off, Pope leaves it alone.
SIX! Gets that one does Buttler. Floated ball on middle, Buttler dances down and heaves it over the long on region for a biggie.
Flatter delivery outside off, Buttler pushes it to point.
Short ball on off, Jos pushes it to cover.
Floated ball on off, Buttler lunges and blocks it to point.
Flatter delivery on off, Buttler cuts but finds the point fielder.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Well fielded! Full delivery outside off, Pope drives it beautifully through covers and picks up a couple. Malan puts in a terrific run and makes a good sliding stop.
Full outside off, left alone.
On off, Pope drives it beautifully but finds the cover fielder.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Pope works it to square leg.

EDGY FOUR! Luck is favouring Ollie Pope out at Newlands. Full delivery on middle, Pope looks to push it but gets a thick outside edge which goes between the second slip and gully fielder. It flies into the fence.
Full delivery on off, Ollie pushes it to cover.
On middle, punched off the back foot.
Full on middle, Buttler comes down the track and pushes it to long on for a single.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and around off, Pope comes down the track and blocks it.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman.
Around off, well defended.

Oh dear...rash, very rash. But this is also a sign that he is looking to be positive. He adopted this technique of walking down the track in the Test matches against India and it worked for him. He is at his best when he is busy. But this time, he walks into the shot, pushes at the ball but misses due to the late movement.
Around off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! SWEET! Full and outside off, Buttler comes forward and drives this through the covers!
Around off, on a length, watchfully blocked out.
Outside off, played through point for a couple.

OUT! Caught behind! Oh my. Did we say Buttler is at his best when he is busy at the crease? He is now gone. Just what South Africa would have wanted before the second new ball is taken. The walk on the move has removed Buttler. Pretorius maintains his line and length outside off and Jos, by habit, looks to push. But the ball nibbles away off the seam and squares him up. There is a noise as the ball goes past the bat and de Kock and Pretorius go up. The finger from the man who matters the most goes up as well. Joseph does not bother waiting. Ultra Edge shows a thin spike. Another start wasted.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
On middle, worked straight to short leg.
Comes down the track this time and drives but finds the bowler.
Full and wide outside off, plenty of flight, Pope reaches out and drives it straight to cover.
Outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Comes down the track now and defends.
Around off, solidly defended.

That was a ripper. On a length outside off, coming back in a long way, Curran looks to work it to the leg side but the ball shapes back in, beats the inside edge, hits the thigh and goes towards gully.
Around off, this is defended stoutly.
Cover drive to mid on. No, I am not done for the day. Yet. Full and outside off, Sam looks to drive but the ball swings back in and goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
This time the cover drive is timed perfectly but straight to cover.

INSIDE EDGE, MISSES THE STUMPS, FOUR! Things are happening here. A length ball outside off, Curran pushes at it away from his body. The ball though, comes in and cramps him for room. The inside edge is eked out and it goes behind, but JUST over the stumps, to the fine leg fence!
Tossed up outside off, driven towards long off for a single.
Oohhh... Curran lunges to defend but the ball spins in, probably off the rough. Don't see much though. It bounces, takes the inside edge but there is no short leg. A run taken towards square leg.
Full and outside off, Pope lunges to defend.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Short and outside off, Ollie rocks back to cut but finds point.
Full again, OP reaches out and blocks.
A length ball outside off, coming in, watchfully defended.
On a length, outside off, coming in with the angle, pushed back to the bowler again.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
Around off, pushed towards mid on.

FOUR! Nicely done. Though, Pretorius will not mind it too much. Not a bad ball, by no means a half volley outside off. Curran has actually come forward and driven a ball which is short of full, on the up. There is a short extra cover and a mid off close to him, in place. But Sam has thread that gap to precision.

OUT! BOWLED! Now, Sir Geoffrey, sir Geoffrey, where are you? Ian Chappell, where art thou? Both of you, if present at the ground, or in the commentary box, would have said, 'Kid, you have a bat in hand. Just make use of that. You are not here to leave balls.' Terrible misjudgement from Sam. Not that a misjudgement is ever sweet. But that is a saying, so went with the flow. A length ball outside off, Curran shoulders arms. But the cherry comes back in with the angle and to his horror, shatters the stumps behind.
Short and outside off, cut straight to point.
Outside off, punched off the back foot.
Full and on middle, Pope comes down the track and looks to flick but hits it in the air. But there is no short leg or short mid-wicket present.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated outside off, driven straight to cover.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.

OUT! Caught behind! Philander strikes with the first ball in his first spell with the second new ball. That is the end of Bess. England in a mess. A typical Vernon dismissal. Ask questions. Put the ball in that avenue of apprehension. Sow the seed of doubt in the batsman's mind. Should I play? Should I leave? Will the ball move away? Will the ball come in? What if I lose my stumps like Curran did? Poor Bess cannot be blamed entirely. He sees that pitch around the 4th stump outside off and is caught in two minds as to which way will the ball move. He looks to play this straight, down the ground but to his dismay, the ball pitches and then straightens. Enough to take the outside edge. Simple catch for Quinton de Kock. 3/10 in 32 balls!
A length ball, around middle, swinging in, Broad misses his flick and is hit on the pads.
Around off, tucked through mid-wicket for a single.
Aha... Movement through the air for Vernon. Outside off, on a length, Ollie flashes a drive but misses.
And again. This is slightly wider outside off, OP launches a massive cover drive, only to miss again.
Goes for the booming inswinger but ends up spraying it on the pads. Pope flicks it towards square leg in the deep for a single.
No looseners. A perfect start. Full and just outside off, watchfully defended.
Around off, defended towards cover.
A bouncer on middle, Pope ducks.
A length ball outside off, Ollie looks to defend but the ball moves away and takes the outside edge. Goes towards point.
Gets the single he wanted. A length ball outside off, OP steers it behind point for a run.

OUT! BOWLED! Broady, Broady, what happened there? Poor lad. 73 matches before he got on the helmet by a vicious Varun Aaron bouncer. Has never been the same since. He is always expecting a bouncer first up. Bowlers all over the world are terrorizing him now, threatening bouncers, but then slipping in fuller ones. Rabada does exactly that. Broad is deep in his crease, expecting a short one. But he gets a fuller one. Now, here is the height of all misfortunes. Stuart does get his bat down. But while coming down, the willow gets stuck behind his front pad! The ball meets no obstruction and clatters the stumps.
Full and wide outside off, Pope slashes hard to sweeper cover. Does not take the single.
Beauty. On a length outside off, Ollie looks to push but the ball moves away late off the seam and beats the outside edge.
Full and straight, pushed towards mid on.
Full and wide outside off, OP drives it through point for a single. 2 balls left for Jimmy to survive.
1 survived. The crowd cheers. Plenty of English supporters today. Full and outside off, Anderson shoulders arms.
Both balls survived. Full and wide outside off, either a bad ball or bowled with a plan to tempt Jimmy into the drive. But it is left alone.
A short ball wide outside off, Pope slashes hard but misses.
A bit wider outside off, Ollie crashes this in front of sweeper, just past cover. Keshav Maharaj has a bit of an area to sweep to his right. So by the time he covers that portion, two runs are taken.
Full and outside off, wide again, OP crashes this through the covers but this time, straight to Maharaj at sweeper.

FOUR! A cheeky shot! A shot which plenty of youngsters love to play these days. That is not to suggest that I am old, by any means. A short ball, around off, coming in with the angle, following the batsman. Pope initially looks to duck but at the last moment, plays the upper cut, right back over the keeper's head! One bounce and into the fence.
Outside off, once again, Ollie looks to play the ramp but misses.

MISCALCULATION! Pope is on his haunches, smiling. That was not how he calculated. A short ball outside off, Pope looks to clobber that back past the bowler. But he mistimes it. Rabada stretches out his left hand but it just eludes him and beats mid off. Now, Anrich Nortje is running after it from mid off and Pope has to think about a single or three. He chooses the latter. Takes two and Jimmy is ready for the third, turning blind. But Pope rightly sends him back, as he is not sure whether he will make it in time to the bowler's end. Good decision in the end as the throw was pretty sharp. But why did he not just settle for a single?
Close call. Full and outside off, Anderson pushes at it away from his body and gets a thick inside edge. It just misses the leg stump, en route fine leg. A single taken.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Down the leg side, worked straight to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Just over! Full and outside off, Pope walks into the shot and lofts it over mid off. Kagiso Rabada moving to his left leaps but the ball goes over him.
FOUR! Much better shot this time. A length ball, on middle, Pope comes down the track and lofts it over mid on. One bounce and into the ropes. 250 UP FOR ENGLAND!
Cheer from the crowd! Jimmy keeps one out from this over. A length ball around off, Anderson gets right behind this one and blocks.
Outside off, another solid defense, to the off side.
Ooohhh... nervy. A length ball outside off, JA looks to play the upper cut, but then misses due to the steep bounce.
Good bowling. Targets the yorker, bowls it very full and straight. But Anderson keeps it out. The crowd cheers again.

Jimmy gets some runs! Well, the crowd has actually stood up as one to applaud. Landed outside off, on a length, JA plays this away from his body and gets it through cover-point. Two runs taken. The stand is worth 20 now, from 23 balls.
A sharp bouncer, outside off, Jimmy looks to fend but the ball keeps on rising and coming in. Beats his poke. Anderson has seen off an entire over.
Short and outside off, cut behind point to get his half century. To NOT get his half century. Team first. First ball. Denies the single.
A length ball outside off, coming in with the angle, Pope looks to tap and run but then changes his mind.
Outside off, flashed through point. No single taken again.
A bouncer on off, Ollie ducks and sways at the same time, in time.

HALF CENTURY FOR OLLIE POPE! Just his second in Tests but it has been his best innings so far in this format. Because it has been under immense pressure. A short ball outside off, Pope pulls it uppishly, through the massive vacant areas at mid-wicket. Dean Elgar gives it a good chase from deep square leg and puts in a slide to stop the ball. Three runs taken.
OOOHH... ALMOST! Full and around middle, Anderson looks to flick and it nearly goes straight to short leg! Lands just short.
That stays low. On a length outside off, Pope stays inside the line and pushes hard but the ball shoots low and beats the inside edge. Lands short of the keeper.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Landed outside off, dabbed to third man. No single taken.

FOUR! There he goes again! What is more interesting is, Faf's reaction. He throws his arms in the air, as if to ask his bowler - 'Why did you bowl that?' Because just before this ball, the captain removed that man from fly slip and got him to second slip. So short ball was definitely not the plan. But Rabada, like a bad student, does not pay heed to his captain's instructions. Bowls it short and Pope ramps it over the keeper, to the third man fence.

CAUGHT OFF A NO BALL! This is really poor from Rabada. First, he does not bowl to the field and second, he has overstepped now. A short ball again, at the body, Pope comes down the track and looks to swat this out of the park. But he is cramped for room and gets a top edge. The ball swirls in the air towards fine leg where Vernon Philander comes running in, does really well to focus on the ball and takes a very good catch. The players are ready to head off the field but umpire Dharmasena wants to check for the overstepping. And yes, replays confirm that Rabada has overstepped. Now, the umpire wants to check whether the batsmen had crossed when the catch was being taken. Yup, the batsmen had crossed, as per the replays. So Anderson will face the remaining two balls of this over. Interestingly, Mike Atherton on air informs us that two balls before Rabada had overstepped but it was not called!
Around middle and leg, tucked towards square leg.
Around middle and leg again, worked towards square leg again. An eventful over, should have been the last of the day and the innings but KG... gone to junior KG.
Short and outside off, cut through point but does not take the single.
Landed outside off, played straight to point.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Short and outside off, cut straight to deep point.
A bouncer, down the leg side, ducked under.
Another bouncer, down the leg side again, ducked under again. OVER AND TIME, says Paul Reiffel. STUMPS ON DAY 1!

Runs straightaway! A fuller ball outside off from Rabada, Anderson dabs it towards gully where the fielder cannot stop the ball cleanly. A single for Anderson on the very first ball. Now, Pope will look to farm the strike from hereon.
Fuller and outside off, it is pushed to covers by Pope.
Yorker around off, Pope jams it out.
Full and on middle again, Pope whips it wide of long on and before the long on fielder can get to the ball, a couple of runs for Pope.
Bouncer on middle and leg. Pope ducks under it with ease.
Quick run! Pope will keep the strike. A back of a length ball on middle, Pope does well to tuck it towards square leg and takes a quick single.
Nortje starts with a good length ball around off, Pope comes forward and blocks it towards mid off.
Shortish around off, tapped towards cover by Pope this time.
Fuller again, Pope pushes it towards sweeper cover. Singles are on offer for Pope but he is not interested. Boundaries are what he is looking for and singles only on the 5th or 6th ball, if possible.
Beaten! First time this morning! Good length ball just outside off, Pope pokes at the ball to get beaten as it straightens a touch.

Goes for the mighty pull to this one but does not make any connection. A back of a length ball on middle, Pope looks to pull but fails. Called one for the over as it was just around Pope's head height.
WIDE! Another bumper which is over the head of Pope and this time the umpire calls it wide. This is around off, Pope lets it be.

Over mid off! Just a single again and Pope keeps the strike again. A short of a length ball outside off, Pope looks to slam it over mid off but mistimes it. However, the timing is good enough to clear Philander at mid off. The batters can get a couple before Philander can get to the ball but only one is what they want.

Oops! Misjudgement on the part of Pope. He thought he'd be able to steal the second but that wasn't on offer. A fuller ball on middle, Pope works it towards long on and takes off for the run. Only a single as the fielder there rushed to the ball quickly. So, 5 potential balls for Anderson to survive.
Anderson does well with the first one he faces. A fuller ball on off, James taps it towards cover.
This time he is beaten but no edge on it so he won't mind. A good length ball around off, Anderson looks to defend but plays down the wrong line to get beaten.
Landed around off, Anderson keeps it out.

OUT! Caught at slip! Rabada has done the job for the Proteas and Anderson cannot manage to see off the over. A shortish ball outside off, Anderson looks to fend at it, away from his body off the back foot. An outside edge is induced and it goes straight to van der Dussen at first slip. ENGLAND ARE ALL OUT FOR 269.
Anderson starts with a good length ball on middle, Elgar defends it out to mid off.
Back of a length ball on off, Elgar defends it out to point.
South Africa and Elgar are underway! Fuller one outside off, Elgar pushes it through covers and crosses over for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Malan defends his first ball in international cricket back to the bowler.
Fullish ball nipping away, Pieter leaves the ball alone to the keeper.

FOUR! First runs for Pieter Malan in Test cricket! This will give him a lot of confidence. Short delivery outside off, Malan stands tall and punches it through the cover region for a boundary. Gives a smile after hitting that shot.
Fuller ball on off first up from Broad. Elgar leans and pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! Punched nicely! First one from Elgar's bat. Another fuller ball around off, Elgar just punches it on the front foot. It races to the long off fence in a jiffy.
Good length ball outside off, it is angled into the left-hander. Elgar covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Landed around off on a good length, Elgar looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes to square leg.

FOUR BYES! That's through everyone. A good length ball which is once again angled into Elgar. He looks to defend but the ball comes back in sharply to beat his inside edge. Buttler behind the wicket fails to collect the ball either. It goes behind him and into the fence.
FOUR! This is a brilliant shot! Full and outside off, Elgar reaches out and drives it through point for another boundary.
Outside off, Malan covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Good length around off, tapped towards covers.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Another leave as Anderson bowls it on a good length ball outside off.
Make that third leave in a row as Malan once again covers his stumps and allows the ball to go to the keeper.
Gets slightly fuller and around off, Malan this time comes forward and defends it.
Shortish length ball outside off, Elgar makes a leave to start the over.
Another ball which is outside off, Elgar has nothing to do with it once again. Broad needs to get closer to the off pole and make Elgar play.
He does that on this one. Bowls it around off and on a slightly fuller length, Elgar gets behind the line of the delivery and defends.
This one is pitched on off and it comes into Elgar. He blocks it off the back foot.
Another one on off, Elgar once again makes a solid block.
Fuller and on off this time, Elgar looks to drive but gets an inside edge. The ball goes between his legs but luckily does not go onto the stumps.
Good length ball on middle, worked towards square leg by Malan for a single.
Fuller and on middle, Elgar works it in front of square leg.
Good length ball on off, Elgar waits and at the last moment taps it towards gully where the fielder does well to stop the ball with a tumble to his left.
On middle, Elgar pushes it to mid on.
Around off, pushed to point.
Nicely done! A fuller ball around off, Elgar runs it down through point and gully and before the fielder can get to the ball, a couple for him.
Good length ball on middle, blocked towards mid-wicket.
Beauty from Broad! Fuller and just outside off. As Malan comes forward to defend the ball shapes away from his and bat. Luckily for him, it does not take the outside edge.
Another ball around off on a fullish length, Malan pushes it to point.
Outside off this time, an easy leave for Malan.
In the channel again but too wide to make Malan play. He shoulders arms.
Another leave to see off the over as Broad dishes out another good length ball outside off.
Good length ball on off, Elgar defends it to mid off.
Fullish delivery outside off, Dean shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on off, Elgar blocks it off the back foot to point.
Fuller ball on off, Elgar solidly defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball on middle and leg, Elgar works it to deep square leg and picks up a couple.

EDGY FOUR! Just short! Good length ball on off, nipping away, Elgar looks to defend it but gets squared up. It goes off the outside edge towards first slip. It bounces in front of him and goes between his legs into the fence.

OUT! Caught! Broad strikes and the debutant has to depart! Brilliant bowling from him. A slightly shortish ball outside off which shapes away after pitching. He can easily let this go to the keeper but this time he has a poke at it. The away movement means an outside edge is induced and it goes to Root at first slip. He takes it in front of his face nicely. Poor, poor shot this one from the debutant.
Fuller ball around off, Hamza comes forward and keeps it out.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Hamza defends it out to mid on.
Length ball on off, Zubayr looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards gully who collects it on a bounce.
On off, Hamza pushes it back to Broad.

BEATEN! Excellent. Just excellent stuff from Broad. Good length ball outside off, moving away from the batsman. Hamza looks to defend off the back foot but fails to get anything on it. A successful over comes to an end from Broad.
FOUR! Curran starts with a poor delivery on the pads, Elgar whips it away to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary. The fielder from deep square leg comes across but gives up the chase.

Another one down the leg side, Elgar flicks it to the deep mid-wicket region and takes three before Crawley from deep square leg hares across and collects it. 7 from the first two balls to start with from Curran.
Better from Curran! Good length ball outside off, Hamza leaves it alone.
On off, Zubayr gets off the mark by guiding this towards point and taking a single.
Fullish delivery on middle, Elgar works it to mid-wicket.
Full ball outside the off stump line, Dean lets the ball go to the keeper.

FOUR! Brilliant shot from Hamza! Positive cricket! That's how he likes to play. Full delivery on off, Hamza leans forward and creams the drive through the cover region for a boundary. Stokes chases after it but does not manage to get there in time.
Good length ball on middle, Zubayr defends it out off the back foot.
On off, driven towards mid off where the fielder dives and stops the ball. No run.
On a length on off, nipping in. Hamza defends it out solidly.

OUT! CAUGHT! Excellent catch from Stokes and Broad gets his second wicket. South Africa are in a spot of bother. Back of a length ball outside off, nipping away. Hamza looks to defend it off the back foot but gets a thick outside edge towards second slip. Stokes there, dives to his right and pouches it just inches above the ground. Brilliant. Broad is making the ball talk from his end at Newlands.
Good length ball on middle, Faf defends it back to the bowler. Broad shows some aggression as he picks the ball and underarms the ball towards du Plessis. Stares exchanged.
Good length on middle and leg, Elgar defends it to mid on.
Fuller one on off, Dean blocks it out to point.
On off, Elgar is solid in defense.
Good length on off, Elgar blocks it out to cover off the back foot.
Fullish one on middle, Dean pushes it to mid off.
On a length on middle, Elgar works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Faf makes a good leave to this one.
Very full delivery on middle, du Plessis pushes it down to mid on.
On a length on off, Faf stands tall and defends it to point.
Fullish delivery outside off, Faf lets the ball go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on off, du Plessis blocks it out.
Nicely bowled! Well played too. Very full delivery on middle, Elgar gets his bat down in time and blocks it out.
Back of a length ball outside off, Elgar pushes it to deep point and takes a single.
Good length ball on middle, du Plessis defends it out to Curran.
Short of a length on middle, Faf works it to square leg and crosses over for a single.
On a length on off, Elgar defends it to cover.
On off, pushed to point for nothing.
Full delivery on middle, Faf defends it to mid on off the front foot.
On a length on middle, du Plessis blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery with extra bounce. Faf looks to defend but it hits the splice of the bat and rolls onto the pitch.
Good length outside off, du Plessis shoulders arms to this one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Anderson returns and picks up the big fish, the South African skipper. Excellent bowling. Full delivery around off, du Plessis looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes to second slip. Stokes stationed there moves to his left and takes a simple catch. The hosts slip further. 40 for 3 in no time. Not the start South Africa would have wanted.
On a length on middle, Rassie defends it out. Excellent over comes to an end from James Anderson.

FOUR! UPPISH BUT SAFE! Bess starts with a floated ball outside off, Elgar lunges forward and looks to drive but it goes uppishly. Luckily for Elgar it goes wide of the diving fielder and into the extra cover fence. Not sure whether the fielder got his hand on it.
Loopy delivery on middle, Dean defends it out.
Floated ball on middle, Elgar works it to the leg side and says no for the single.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on middle, Dean works it to mid-wicket.
Looped up ball on middle, Elgar pushes it back to Bess.
On a length outside off, moving in a bit. van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball outside off, Rassie does not fiddle with it and lets it through to the keeper.

EDGY FOUR! Things are happening here at Newlands. Fortunate way to get off the mark for van der Dussen. Back of a length ball outside off, Rassie pokes at it but gets a thick outside edge which goes between the second slip and the gully fielder. Stokes dives to his right but the ball goes quickly past him and into the fence.
On a length outside off, this time van der Dussen shoulders arms to it.
Good length delivery on middle, Rassie defends it to short leg.
Full delivery on off, van der Dussen defends it to the off side.
Loopy delivery on off, Elgar pushes it to cover and picks up a single.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, van der Dussen works it to deep square leg and takes a single. 50 up for the Proteas.
Flat one on off, Elgar rocks back and blocks it to cover.
Looped up ball outside off, Elgar pushes it to cover.
On off, Dean defends it off the back foot.
Tosses this one up on middle, Elgar gently pushes it back to the bowler.
Fullish delivery on off, Rassie defends it to cover.

BEATEN! That is a peach of a delivery. Good length delivery around off, moving away from the batsman. Rassie attempts to defend but it just whizzes past the outside edge of the bat and into the keeper's gloves.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on off, Rassie guides it to point.
Fuller one outside off, Rassie lunges and then decides to leave the ball alone.
Fullish ball outside off, van der Dussen makes a good leave to the keeper.
Flatter one outside off, Elgar leaves it alone.
Fuller one on middle and leg, Elgar pushes it down to long on for a single.
Looped up ball on off, Rassie prods forward and defends it out.
Flatter one on middle, van der Dussen defends it to short leg.
Floated on off, pushed to cover for a single.
On middle, Elgar solidly defends it back to the bowler.

NOT OUT! Rassie van der Dussen is survived by a big inside edge. Full delivery on middle, van der Dussen looks to push but misses to get hit on the pads. There were two noises though. Anderson and the rest appeal. The umpire agrees and gives it out. Rassie has gone for the DRS straightaway. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there was an inside edge. The umpire will have to overturn his decision. Brilliant to review the on-field call. Had he missed, it would have been plumb.
Good length ball on off, Rassie pushes it to point and takes a single.
Full delivery on off, pushed through covers for a couple.
The batsman has driven it through mid off.
On off, defended to cover.
Good length on middle, Elgar works it to the leg side and picks up a single.
Flatter one on middle, Elgar works it to the leg side.
On off, defended off the front foot to cover.
Fullish on middle, Elgar plays it down to long on for a single.
Looped up ball on middle and leg, Rassie defends it to short leg.
Flat one on middle and leg, van der Dussen works it to square leg and crosses over for a single.
Floats this one up on off, Elgar defends it out to point.
Stokes starts with a good length ball on off, van der Dussen defends it off the back foot.
Fuller one outside off, Rassie shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! What a ball from Stokes! Fuller one in the channel of uncertainty, moves away. Rassie looks to defend but misses it altogether.
On middle, flicked to deep mid-wicket and a couple is taken before the fielder can clean it up.
On a length outside off, van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Full one outside off, Rassie van der Dussen lets the ball go to the keeper. LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Curran starts with a full delivery on middle, Elgar pushes it down to mid on.
Good length on middle, Elgar works it to backward square leg and picks up a couple.
Fullish on off, Elgar lunges forward and pushes it to cover.
FOUR! That is a fine, fine shot from Elgar. Curran dishes a half volley on middle, Elgar prods forward and creams the drive through mid on for the first boundary of the session.
Back of a length on off, Elgar taps it to gully.
On off, Dean defends it out.
Broad returns with a full delivery on off, Rassie pushes it to cover and crosses over for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Elgar works it to mid-wicket.
Fullish on middle, Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Valiant effort from Denly! Short of a length delivery down the leg side, Elgar just helps it on its way to fine leg. Denly comes across, dives but in the end the ball touches the ropes.
On off, defended to mid off.
On a length on off, Elgar pushes it to deep cover and will keep strike for the next over.
Back of a length on off, Elgar punches it to backward point and crosses over for a single.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Rassie flicks it to mid-wicket.
Just short! Fuller one outside off, van der Dussen looks to push at it but it takes the outside edge. It goes on the bounce to the gully fielder.
On middle, Rassie blocks it out onto the pitch.
FOUR! Sumptuous! Not a great delivery from Curran as well. Full delivery on off, van der Dussen lunges forward and creams the drive through extra cover for a boundary.
On off, Rassie defends it out.
Full delivery outside off, Elgar lets the ball go to the keeper.
Back of a length on off, Elgar stands tall and pushes it to point.
Full delivery on off, Dean pushes it to cover.
Well fielded! Fullish delivery down the leg side, Elgar works it down to fine leg and picks up a couple to move to 49. Denly comes across and slides to clean it up.

FIFTY! 14th one for Elgar in Tests. He has looked the only comfortable out there but he knows that it is only half the job done. Needs to continue to score a big one there and get his side closer to England's score. He gets there by guiding this length ball on off to point and taking a single.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Fullish delivery outside off, Dean leaves the ball alone.
Good length ball on off, Elgar guides it to point.
FOUR! Poor bowling! Cannot bowl there at this pace. Short delivery on middle, Elgar camps back and pulls it to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Back of a length ball on middle, Dean blocks it back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Elgar pushes it to deep cover and calls for a single.
On off, pushed to deep cover for a single.

BEATEN! What a delivery from Stuart Broad! How come that did not take the edge? Good length ball on off, nipping away, Rassie looks to defend but misses it altogether. Broad starts celebrating but sees that no one else is supporting him so he backs out.
Full delivery on middle, van der Dussen looks to flick it but gets hit on the pads.

OUT! CAUGHT! No it's not! It is a NO BALL and Broad returns the gift which Rabada gave in the first innings. This was a peach of a delivery though from Broad. Good length delivery around off, Rassie van der Dussen looked to defend it off the back foot but the ball suddenly got a lift. The batsman could do nothing and just managed a glove back to the keeper. Buttler pouched it safely. The umpire gave it out and Rassie started walking. But wait, he was told to stay back as the on-field umpires wanted to check for the no ball. The replas rolled in and it showed that Broad had overstepped by a big margin! Luck,luck that's all we can say for Rassie van der Dussen out there.
Good length ball outside off, van der Dussen drives it through covers for three before  the fielder can come across and clean it up. 50 run stand is up between the two.
Good length around off, Elgar looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge almost rolling on to stumps. Elgar though, gets his bat in between and pushes it away.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full delivery on off, Dean pushes it to cover.
Landed outside off, spinning in, worked strai9ght to short mid-wicket.
Full and around middle, van der Dussen drives this straight back but Bess dives to his right and makes a half-stop, parrying the ball to short mid-wicket.
Full and tossed up outside off, smothered away.
Around middle, worked straight to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up again, Rassie leans and pushes this through the covers for a single.
Landed outside off, a puff of dust is emanated as the ball lands on the rough generated from the footmarks, Elgar lets it go.

FOUR! Lovely from Rassie van der Dussen. Fullish ball to start from Stokes. Van der Dussen makes a good stride forward and creams the drive through extra covers for a boundary. It is uppish for a while but it is in the gap. The replays show that Stokes had overstepped by a big margin but it was not given. Wonder what is the umpire doing out there. It happened in South Africa's first innings as well.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on off, pushed to point.
Full delivery outside off, Rassie shoulders arms.
Back of a length delivery on off, Rassie punches it to point.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated ball on off, Elgar leans forward and pushes it to point.
Flat one on middle, Dean defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish on middle, Elgar plays it wide of the bowler, towards mid on. No run.
Flatter delivery outside off, Elgar pushes it to deep cover and crosses over for a single.
Tosses this one up on middle, Rassie looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge which goes towards square leg. A single taken.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler off the front foot.
Back of a length on off, Rassie camps back and blocks it to cover.
Short of a length ball on middle, Rassie pulls it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
Fullish on middle, Elgar works it through mid-wicket and picks up a couple. Broad hares after it and collects it. 100 up for the hosts.
Good length ball down the leg side, Elgar looks to flick but misses it.
Back of a length ball on middle, Elgar hops and blocks it to Stokes.
OUCH! That is nasty! Short delivery on middle, Elgar hops to defend but gets hit on the gloves. It just bounces short of the first slip fielder. No harm done.
Tossed up delivery on middle and leg, Rassie works it to mid-wicket.
Fuller one outside off, van der Dussen pushes it to cover.
Looped up ball on off, defended out solidly.
FOUR! That's an excellent shot from Rassie van der Dussen. Floated ball outside off, Van der Dussen takes a good stride forward and drives it through extra cover for a boundary.
Floated on middle, Rassie blocks it out.
Flighted ball on middle, Rassie is solid in defense.
Short delivery around middle and leg, Elgar pulls it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
Good length ball on the pads, Rassie works it to deep square leg and takes a run. The replays show that is another no ball from Stokes but not given. Horrendous umpiring.

Close! Full delivery on off, Elgar pushes it to cover-point and takes off for a quick run. The fielder comes across and then has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Had he hit, Elgar would have been in though as the dive he made would have saved him. He seems to have hurt himself in the process.
Short of a length on middle, Rassie pulls it to the leg side for a single.
Fullish ball outside off, Elgar leaves it alone.
On off, defended out to the bowler.
Floated ball on middle, van der Dussen pushes it down to long on for a single.
Looped up ball on middle, Elgar works it to leg side.
On off, defended it to the off side.
Loopy delivery on off, Dean defends it to point.
Flighted outside off, Dean drives it to cover.
Floated on middle, Dean works it to mid on.
Full one on off, Rassie pushes it to mid off.
Fuller one on off, van der Dussen pushes it through covers and picks up a couple.
Good length ball on middle, Rassie works it to deep mid-wicket and takes another couple before the fielder can clean it up from deep mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, Rassie defends it back to the bowler.
Short of a length on middle, Rassie looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. It goes towards the leg side and a leg bye is taken.
On middle, Dean works it to the leg side and crosses over for a single.
Floated on off, Elgar pushes it to cover.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on middle, Elgar whips it to square leg.
Loopy delivery on middle, Elgar defends it out to the off side.
Tossed up delivery outside off, Elgar pushes it past the diving fielder towards deep cover for a single.
Flatter delivery on middle, Rassie flicks it to square leg.
Anderson returns with a good length ball outside off, Elgar lets the ball through to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on off, Elgar guides it to point and crosses over for a single.
On a length on middle and leg, Rassie defends it to the leg side.
Back of a length delivery on off, Rassie hops and defends it off the back foot. Anderson stumbles on his followthrough.
On a length on middle, Rassie works it to mid-wicket.
OHH! Fuller delivery outside off, moving in a little. Rassie makes a good leave to this one.
Floated ball on off, Elgar pushes it to short cover.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Elgar pushes it down to long on for a run.
Tossed up ball on middle, Rassie defends it out.
Full on off, pushed to cover.
Flatter delivery on middle, whipped to square leg.
Loopy delivery outside off, Rassie leans forward and drives it through covers for a single.
Back of a length delivery on off, Rassie hops and defends it to cover.

JUST SHORT! Stokes signals it has not carried! Brilliant delivery on off, Rassie van der Dussen looks to defend it out but takes the thick outside edge.
