It goes towards Stokes at second slip and he dives to his left and collects. There is some excitement but Stokes gets up and signals it has bounced in front of him. He is having all the luck in this game so far.
Fuller one outside off, moving in. Rassie lets the ball go to the keeper.
On off, defends it off the back foot.
On a length on off, van der Dussen defends it to point.
Fuller delivery on middle, Rassie pushes it to mid on for nothing.
Floated ball on middle, Elgar pushes it down to long on and crosses over for a single.
Fullish on off, Rassie leans and pushes it to deep cover for a single.
Flatter one outside off, Elgar guides it to point.
Loopy one on off, Elgar prods forward and blocks it to cover.
On off, pushed to the cover fielder.
Flat one on middle, Dean defends it to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Rassie defends it solidly to cover.
On a length on off, Rassie looks to defend but it takes the inside half of his bat and rolls to square leg. The batters manage to pinch a single.
Fullish on off, Elgar pushes it to mid off.
Fuller one outside off, Elgar drives it to deep cover. But before Sam Curran can come across from deep point, the batters take a couple.
On a length on middle, Elgar defends it to point.
Fullish outside off, Elgar leaves the ball alone.
Full and around off, solidly defended.
Full on middle, pushed towards mid on for a single. Sorry, long on. For some reason, Joe Root is offering these easy singles.
There is another one. On middle and leg, now Elgar pushes this towards long on for a run.
Fired in from around the wicket on middle, van der Dussen blocks it in a hurry.
Thrown up outside off, driven away from his body, through the covers, for one.
Almost a yorker, outside off, pretty full, Elgar digs it out.
Full and outside off, that stays low, van der Dussen brings his bat down in time to defend.
Wide outside off, left alone.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
A good length ball, outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and just outside off, Rassie gets a big stride forward to block it towards cover.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Short and outside off, cut straight to point.
Full and around off, pushed towards long on for a single.
Action replay of the previous delivery.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full again, watchfully blocked out.
On middle, pushed towards the bowler.

EDGED, DROPPED! Ben Stokes, off all the people. Anderson does the hard work, bowls it on a length outside off and makes Rassie go for the drive. The outside edge is taken and it goes to second slip. A dive is required from the fielder and Ben Stokes does dive. Goes one-handed. Now, a catch needs to be taken and Stokes takes it too! But just when he takes the catch with a dive to his right, his right elbow hits the ground and the ball pops out. Stokes has his hands on his head. If looks could kill, Anderson has the 'Meet-me-after-office' type one.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and just outside off, watchfully defended.
On a good length outside off, defended awkwardly.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
That is a snorter. On a length outside off, van der Dussen feels for it but the ball suddenly kicks up after pitching. Just about beats the outside edge. A testing over from Jimmy.
Full and wide outside off, left alone.
Closer than the previous one, left alone again.
Short and outside off, punched straight to cover.
A bit of round-arm from Joe Root, full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and around middle now, pushed back to Joe again.
Full and straight, driven back to Root.
Full and outside off, left alone.
Outside off, punched off the back foot for a single. The stand moves to 90 now. South Africa trail by 139.
Outside off, pushed through point for a single to get to 70.
That nips back in off the deck, Rassie looks to defend but the ball cuts him into half. Beats the bat and hits the pad.
Full and outside off, Rassie pushes this with a loose bottom hand and the ball goes uppishly, but well wide of the bowler, towards mid off.
Full and outside off, van der Dussen comes forward to defend but the ball takes the outside edge. Does not carry to gully.
Outside off, punched off the back foot for a single. That was uppish, but well wide of the diving short mid-wicket.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, punched through the covers. The batsmen take the second on the throw and a better one could have had Elgar at the bowler's end.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Down the leg side, flick shot missed.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, Elgar comes forward and blocks.

FOUR! That is really good work. Takes the partnership to 98. A half tracker, around middle, coming at a very nice height for the batsman, around tummy high, Elgar does not miss out. Swivels and pulls it through square leg for a boundary. It is very important that England sustain the pressure built up by Anderson.

Full on middle, Dean pushes it with soft hands towards short mid-wicket. First, he asks his partner to wait, then, when he sees the fielder misfield, calls for two. But later, he sees Stuart Broad get across to his left from mid on and shouts a loud NO. So just a single in the end.
Around middle, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, driven straight to short extra cover.
Around off, pushed back with a loose bottom hand.
Full and down the leg side, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
There he was, chasing a wide one. Full and outside off, hits the footmarks, generates a puff of dust, Elgar looks to drive but misses.
100-RUN STAND IS UP! Slowly and surely, South Africa are making themselves comfortable in the driver's seat. Around middle, rucked through square leg for a run.
Full and around middle, pushed towards short mid-wicket.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full and just outside off, watchfully defended back to the bowler.
Full again, around off, Elgar brings his bat down at the last moment to defend.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Down the leg side, Elgar misses his flick and the ball goes off his pads towards square leg. A leg bye taken.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler with an ugly, awkward stance. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2, SA TRAIL BY 128!
Starts with a full delivery on off, Elgar pushes it to cover.
Flatter delivery outside off, Dean lets the ball go to the keeper.
Fullish on middle, Dean plays it back to Bess.
On middle, Elgar pushes it back to the bowler.
Flat one on off, Elgar blocks it to point.
Floated on middle, Dean defends it back to the bowler.
Broad starts with a fuller one on off, van der Dussen drives it to mid off.
On a length on off, Rassie defends it to cover for nothing.
Fullish on off, Rassie solidly blocks it out.
Fuller one on off, driven nicely towards mid off where the fielder slides and makes a stop.
Good length delivery outside off, keeping low, Rssie does not fiddle with it and lets it go through to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Rassie defends it to the off side. Maiden over from Broad.
Floated on off, Elgar defends it to cover.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Floats this up, does Bess! Elgar strides forward and lofts it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Looped up ball on middle, Elgar works it to the leg side and takes a single.
Flatter one on middle and leg, Rassie is solid in defense.
On off, van der Dussen defends it out.
Tossed up ball outside off, van der Dussen pushes it to cover for another dot.
Good length ball on off, Elgar looks to defend but it hits the under edge of the bat rolling going onto hit the boot. Elgar has hurt himself due to that.
On a length on middle, Dean tucks it to deep square leg and takes a run.
Shot! Full delivery outside off, van der Dussen drives it nicely but it goes on one bounce to the cover fielder.
Good length ball on off, Rassie defends it to cover.

FOUR! FIFTY! Back-to-back fifties for Rassie van der Dussen in Tests! Brilliant innings. On a length outside off, Rassie opens the face of his bat and then guides it past the diving fielder at gully. It rolls into the fence. Can he convert this to a maiden ton?
Outside off, left alone by Rassie.
Loopy delivery on off, Elgar prods and defends it out.
Floated on off, Elgar pushes it to cover.
On middle, pushed down to long on for a single.
Flatter delivery on middle, Rassie tucks it to square leg.
Loops this one up on middle, Rassie solidly blocks it.
Floated one on middle, Rassie goes on his front foot and blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Elgar works it to square leg.
Fullish on off, Dean taps it towards point and calls van der Dussen for a quick single. What is happening? Another no ball not called by the umpire.
On a length outside off, van der Dussen leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone.

OHH! How did that miss the stumps? It's all about luck for Rassie van der Dussen in this innings so far. Back of a length on off, keeping a little low, Rassie looks to defend but it sneaks under his bat and goes just over the off stump.
On a length outside off, Rassie lets the ball go to the keeper.
Floated on off, Elgar pushes it to point.
Full on middle, Dean plays it back to Bess.
Looped up ball on middle, Dean works it to square leg.
Shorter outside off, Elgar pushes it to point for nothing.
On middle and off, Elgar strides forward and blocks it.
Tosses this one up on middle, Elgar works it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery outside off, too wide to trouble van der Dussen to play at it.
Fullish delivery on off, bouncing a touch more. Rassie looks to defend but gets hit on the gloves. It rolls to point.
Fuller delivery outside off, Rassie pushes this to cover.
On middle, pushed towards mid on for a dot ball.
On a length on middle, Rassie whips it wide of mid on and crosses over for a single.
Short of a length down the leg side, Elgar tucks it to fine leg and keeps strike for the next over.
Tossed up on middle, Elgar pushes this down to long on and takes a single.
Flatter one on middle, Rassie works it to square leg.
Bess tosses this one on middle, Rassie prods forward and plays it back to the bowler.
Flatter one on middle, van der Dussen plays it to the leg side.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Rassie whips it but it hits the short leg fielder on the boot.
On middle, pushed to mid-wicket. Rassie wants the run but Elgar sends him back.
Short delivery down the leg side, Elgar plays the pull down to fine leg and takes a single.
Fullish on middle, Rassie pushes it to mid on.
On a length on off, van der Dussen defends it to cover.
Too wide outside off, Rassie has no problems in leaving it alone.
BOUNCER! Nicely bowled this! It is bowled around middle, Rassie looks to hook at first but then decides to leave it at the last moment. It will count as a play and a miss.
Another bumper on middle and leg, this time Rassie ducks under it.
Floated one on off, Elgar defends it out.
Loopy delivery on off, Elgar looks to drive it but hits the bottom edge and goes back to the bowler.
On middle, defended out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ho ho ho! Are we dreaming? No, we are not! A wicket indeed has fallen. And this time, IT IS NOT A NO BALL. A poor shot from Elgar. Very rarely do we see him doing this but he has thrown it away after playing an excellent innings. He and van der Dussen were running away with the game and this might just bring the visitors back in it. Bess floats this one up outside off, Elgar strides forward and looks to lift it over mid off. However, the ball is not that full to be hit on the rise. He is already through his shot and there is extra bounce on that one. Hence, he does not time it well and it goes high up in the air. Root moves back from mid off and takes the catch. Not easy to catch those. A 100 was there for the taking for Elgar but it was not to be. Elgar is disappointed and looks up to the skies as trudges back to the pavillion. So what is the deficit? 112. Can England get another before it trickles into double digits? Sorry, cannot say trickles. Because the man coming in next will not allow the run rate to trickle down.
On middle, flicked to short leg.
Loopy delivery on middle, Rassie blocks it out.
Fullish delivery on middle and leg, Quinton de Kock whips it to deep square and picks up a couple to get off the mark. The fielder comes across from deep square leg and cleans it up.
On a length outside off, de Kock punches it to deep point and takes off for a quick couple before the fielder can hare across and throw it back to the keeper.
Fullish outside off, Quinton leaves the ball alone to the keeper.
Good stop! Full delivery on middle, de Kock pushes it back and Stokes jumps and makes the stop with his left hand. Saved some runs there.
On off, pushed to point.
Short of a length ball on middle and leg, Quinton works it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
Floats this one on off, Quinton pushes it to cover.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, de Kock defends it out.
EDGY FOUR! Lucky for de Kock. Flighted ball outside off, de Kock looks to drive it but gets an outside edge past the first slip fielder and into the third man fence.
Short delivery outside off, Quinton cuts it nicely through point. Broad hares after it and collects it. Two taken.
Floated on middle, de Kock pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length on middle, Rassie works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! That is a long hop, on middle, van der Dussen rocks back and pulls it through mid-wicket and gets a boundary!
Outside off, Rassie looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. The ball does not carry to the gully fielder.
FOUR! That is a bad ball. Down the leg side, tickled to the fine leg fence.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
A length ball outside off, Rassie shoulders arms.
Full on middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
On middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a run.
Full on middle, pushed through mid on for one.
Full and outside off, smothered back to the bowler.
Outside off, driven back to the bowler again.
Outside off, Rassie pokes at it and gets a thick outside edge. It goes behind gully. A run taken.
A length ball outside off, left alone.
A bouncer now, on middle, ducked under.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
A length ball on middle, tucked through mid-wicket for a run.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Full and around middle, watchfully defended towards short leg.
Outside off, pushed through mid on for a single.
Landed outside off, a touch wide, let through.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
On middle, pushed through mid on for a run.
Landed around off, tucked towards short leg.
A length ball, on middle, tucked through square leg for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Landed outside off, played straight to point.
Full and around off, van der Dussen looked to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
On middle, flicked through mid-wicket for a run.
Full and around off, defended in front of short leg.
Around off, a touch short, worked past short leg for a single.
Full and around off, pushed towards the bowler.
Landed outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Up and over! That is de Kock as we all know. Full and outside off, Quinton comes down the track and lofts it over mid off. Two bounces and into the ropes.
Full and outside off, pushed with a lunge through the covers for a single.
Curran starts with a fullish ball on middle, Quinton pushes it towards mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT! What has Quinton de Kock done here? Everybody knows that he loves to play positive cricket but was there any need of that shot? Just like yesterday, the last session is seeing wickets. Curran's change in pace has done in de Kock here. He rolls his fingers on the ball and lands it on a length outside off. Quinton is early into his shot as he looks to heave and gets a leading edge. It goes high up in the air towards mid off. James Anderson moves to his left from mid off and takes a simple catch. QdK is dejected and looks at the ground before walking off. Has this game opened up again? The deficit is 78. We might be in for a shout regarding a one-inning shootout.
BEATEN! Lovely followup delivery to Philander. Good length outside off, Vernon looks to defend it but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and into the mitts of the keeper.
On a length on middle, Philander defends this one solidly.
On off, pushed to cover.
Short of a length outisde off, Philander pushes it to deep point and takes a single.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter one outside off, Vernon pushes it to cover.
Loopy delivery on middle, Philander defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery outside off, Philander leans forward and drives it through extra cover. Two taken before the fielder comes across and cleans it up.
Flat one on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Tosses this one up on middle, Vernon plays it towards mid off.
On a length on off, Rassie defends it to point and takes a single.
Good length ball on off, Vernon defends it off the back foot to mid off.
Back of a length ball on middle, Philander camps on his back foot and defends it out onto the pitch.
Fullish delivery on off, Vernon drives it straight to the cover fielder.
On off, Philander drives but cannot pierce the gap at cover.
Back of a length ball around off, Vernon drops his wrists and guides this towards the third man region. The fielder comes across, slides and makes the stop. Two taken.
Loopy on off, defended off the front foot.
Outside off, van der Dussen lunges and defends it to the point region for a single.
Flatter one on middle, Vernon solidly defends it out.
Tosses this one on off, Philander pushes it to cover.
Flatter one on off, Philander blocks it to point.
On off, driven towards mid off for nothing.
Good length ball on middle, Rassie works it to mid-wicket.
Fullish ball on middle and leg, van der Dussen pushes it down to mid on.
On off, pushed towards deep cover and takes a run.
On a length on off, Philander guides it to gully who collects it on the bounce.
Good length ball on off, Philander taps it to the off side and takes another run. 200 up for the hosts.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another one bites the dust! Sam Curran does it again for England. Stokes takes a brilliant catch at second slip. Indecision costs Rassie his wicket. He is not sure whether to come forward or not but his basic foot movement is to plant his left foot forward, almost like a reflex action. Now, this is a good length ball outside off and van der Dussen has his left foot planted across. When you do that, it is very difficult to leave balls. The cherry is a touch wide but RvdD has already made up his mind to run this down to third man. Then, when he sees the line, he thinks he can leave it alone. But alas, it is too late. The ball lands and then bounces a touch high. Van der Dussen is in no man's land, just hanging his bat with its face open. The ball takes the outside edge and flies behind. Ben Stokes at slip number 2 dives to his right and takes an excellent catch with both hands. Rassie has to go after playing an excellent knock. South Africa needed him to stay till the end tonight. The deficit is reading 69 and there are still 9 overs left in the day.
Around middle, defended watchfully to the leg side.
A touch short, kicks up, but Philander plays it down in front of short leg.
A touch short, tucked towards short leg, who tries to duck but the ball hits his back.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Tossed up outside off, defended to the off side.

Down the leg side, Philander tucks it towards fine leg. Stuart Broad chases it down from backward square leg but then the hadada comes in his way. He tries to be cautious, fearing that the ball will hit the bird, but it calmly hops across, perfectly giving way to the ball. The crowd cheers that. A single taken.
Fuller one on off, Philander drives it to mid off.
Back of a length on off, Vernon stands tall and defends it to cover.
Outside off, Vernon makes a leave to the keeper.
On a length on middle, VP solidly plays it back to the bowler.
Short of a length outside off, Philander pushes it to deep cover and takes a single.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Floated one on middle, Vernon defends it to short leg.
On off, Philander defends it to cover.
Flatter one outside off, Vernon pushes it towards point and a single is taken.
Floated ball on off, Pretorius lunges forward and pushes it to cover.
Full one on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
TOP EDGE AND FOUR! Lucky! Short of a length ball on middle and leg, Pretorius looks to sweep it but it goes off his top edge and over the short fine leg fielder. It rolls onto the fence.
Good length ball on off, Vernon looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards gully.
EDGY BUT SAFE! Fullish outside off, Philander looks to push but gets an outside edge to second slip. Stokes dives a little to his right to catch it but it bounces just short of him.
On off, defended off the back foot.
Fuller one outside off, Vernon leaves it alone.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Philander ducks under it.
Fullish outside off, Vernon has no problems in leaving this one alone.

DROPPED! Lady luck is with South Africa today! The second new ball almost did the trick! Good length ball swinging away from the batsman. Pretorius looks to defend but takes the outside edge going towards second slip. Stokes usually does not drop those but this one he puts one down. He bends on his knees to his left, gets two hands to it but does not hold on. Probably he was worried whether the ball will carry to him or not.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length ball on off, Pretorius defends it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ben Stokes does not drop this one and the new ball actually does the trick in the end. Fullish delivery on off, moving away a lot. Pretorius looks to push at it but it goes off the outside edge to second slip. Stokes, ohh Stokes, drops one and takes another. He moves to his right and pouches it with both hands. This was a tough catch and Stokes has done wonderfully well. Wait, the sideways replay rolls in and it shows that Ben had caught it with just one hand. The left hand came to it late. For a change, luck favouring England.
On a length on off, defended back to the bowler.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot. The batsmen have run through for a single.

A ripper to start! Boy, is this second new ball talking or what? 3 overs and 5 balls left now for the end of day's play. Full and outside off, delivered with a scrambled seam, Maharaj pushes at it tentatively but the ball moves away, just enough, to beat the outside edge.
Good length ball outside off, Maharaj lets this ball go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Maharaj does not need to play at that! This is poor batting. Full delivery wide outside off, nipping away. Keshav goes on his front foot in an attempt to defend but misses it altogether.

Well played from Maharaj! Fuller one outside off, Maharaj leans forward and drives it through covers. Joe Denly hares after it and makes a sliding stop. The umpires check whether it is a clean save and the replays show that it is. Average running though. Maharaj wants the third but Philander drops his gloves at the bowler's end. So only two in the end.
Short of a length outside off, Maharaj looks to play it at first but then decides to leave it alone.
On off, defended out by Maharaj.

BEATEN! The new ball is doing all sorts of things out there in the middle. Beautiful bowling from Anderson. Full delivery around off swinging away. Philander looks to defend it off the front foot but misses it altogether due to the swing on it.
On a length on off, Vernon defends it to cover.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Shot! Full delivery outside off, Vernon drives it through covers and picks up three before the fielder can come across and collect it before the ball reaches the ropes.
Good length on middle and leg, Maharaj works it to backward square leg and takes a single.
Well left in the end. Full delivery outside off, this one coming in. Vernon makes a good leave to that one.
Good length ball on middle, Maharaj defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish on off, Keshav taps it to point for nothing.
BEATEN! That is a snorker of a delivery! Short of a length outside off, Maharaj plays it well as he drops his wrists at the last moment and sways away from it.
Full delivery on off, Maharaj drives it to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Maharaj defends it to cover.
Good length ball on off, Keshav pushes it to the cover fielder.
Full delivery on middle, Philander defends it out off the front foot.
Outside off, left alone by Philander. 4 more balls for him to survive the day.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Philander works it to square leg and crosses over for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! A wicket to end the day! That is a terrific ball. It ends a brilliant session for England. On a length on off, nipping in, Maharaj looks to flick but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads. It then lobs off to third slip where Sibley takes the catch running forward. Anderson first appeals for LBW but then sees Dominic Sibley taking the catch. He appeals again and Kumar Dharmasena, the on-field umpire gives it out signaling that it has hit the inside edge. STUMPS ON DAY 2, SA TRAIL BY 54!

OUT! CAUGHT! What a start to Day 3 for England! That is some bowling from James Anderson! On a length, outside off, nipping away. Rabada looks to defend this with little to no foot movement and the ball takes a faint outside edge back to Buttler who makes no mistake. Anderson appeals and the umpire raises his finger. A wicket off the last ball of Day 2 and now a wicket off the first ball on Day 3. Anderson is on fire.
Yes, he can! Anderson bowls a good length ball outside off, Nortje leaves this ball alone.
BEATEN! Wild drive from Philander! Full delivery outside off, Philander looks to play an expansive drive to this one but fails to get any bat on it.
On a length outside off, hitting a crack on the pitch, causing it to bounce a little more. Philander looks to punch but misses it altogether due to the extra bounce on it.
On a length on off, Philander looks to defend but goes off the outside edge and rolls towards gully.
On off, defended off the back foot.
Fuller one on off, Vernon pushes it to deep cover and takes a single. Nortje has to survive one ball of Broad now.
Fullish outside off, Anrich shoulders arms to it.

Would have been gone for all money! There was no run there but both the batters went for it. Good length ball on off, Vernon gets a thick edge towards gully and takes off for a run. Pope there dives to his right and gathers the ball. Pope throws it at the keeper's end but misses the stumps. Had he hit, Nortje would have been out by a mile. He was not even in the frame as the replays rolled in. Wondering why would Philander want to take a single off the first ball and give Nortje the strike so soon in his innings?
BEATEN! Beautiful from Anderson. Fullish delivery around off, Nortje looks to defend but gets squared up. He misses and the ball goes into the mitts of the keeper.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off, Nortje leaves it alone.
FOUR! Lovely batting from Nortje. The trail is now below 50. Full delivery on the pads, Nortje flicks it beautifully to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
On a length on off, Anrich attempts to defend but takes the inside edge and hits the pads. The ball rolls to point for no run.
On a length on middle, Philander goes on his toes and defends.
Outside off, pushed towards point for a single. 4 balls for Nortje to negotiate in this over now.
Bouncer outside off, Nortje awkwardly sways away from it.
Fullish delivery outside off, Nortje lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Fullish on middle, Anrich pushes it down to mid on.
On off, Nortje defends it well towards cover. That will be the end of another over and Nortje is doing well, for now at least.
Full delivery on middle, Vernon blocks it towards mid off and a single is taken.
On a length on off, Anrich pushes it to point.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and leg, Nortje looks to duck but falls down in the process.
Another bumper around off this time, Anrich ducks under it comfortably.
Good length delivery on middle, Anrich defends it out to mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT! 5-fer for James Anderson, his 28th in Test cricket! Brilliant from Stokes as well as he takes a stunning catch in the slip cordon. This is a terrific ball from James Anderson. A good length ball outside off, inducing the drive from Anrich Nortje. The batter obliges but he manages just an outside edge on it. The ball flies to the right of first slip and to the left of second slip. Stokes from second slip dives to his left and takes a superb catch to end the South African innings. Stokes takes his 5th catch of this innings and becomes the first outfield English player to do so. All smiles for the England players as they return to the pavilion.
Rabada starts with a length ball outside off, it is left alone by Zak Crawley.
FOUR! England are underway and in style! Full ball on the pads, Crawley flicks this one off his pads and the ball races away to the mid-wicket fence.
Again Rabada bowls one outside off, Crawley leaves it alone.
On off again, driven to the man at mid off.
FOUR! Crawley has come out as a confident man here. This time it is a full ball on off by Rabada, Crawley gets on the front foot and just drives it through mid off for a boundary.

Rabada ends the over by bowling a length ball on middle, Crawley looks to defend but the ball goes off the inside edge and rolls towards fine leg. Good start to the innings for England as 8 runs come off the over.
Philander starts with a good length ball on middle, Sibley defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball on off, Dominic defends it towards cover.
Fullish delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Sibley defends this good length ball on middle and leg towards the man mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Sibley pushes it to point off the front foot.
Fuller one on off, Sibley blocks it out onto the pitch.
Short delivery on off, Zak looks to pull but is early into his shot. He gets hit on the body and the ball rolls back to the keeper.
On a length on off, Crawley solidly defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball on middle, Crawley works it through square leg and takes a couple before the fielder can clean it up.
Full delivery nipping in a little, Crawley makes a good leave to this one.
Back of a length ball outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it.
On middle and leg, worked to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on off, Sibley defends it back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Dominic does not fiddle with it and shoulders arms to it.
Good length delivery on off, Sibley defends it to point.
Outside off, left alone by Sibley.
Sibley is away! Good length ball on middle, Sibley works it to backward square leg and picks up a couple.
On a length outside off, Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
Good length delivery on off, keeping a little low. Crawley gets his bat down in time and defends it to the leg side.
Nasty!!! Short of a length ball on off, Crawley looks to pull the ball but it hits the edge of the bat and goes onto hit the grill of the helmet.
Fullish delivery outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball on off, Crawley defends it to the off side.

BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and leg, Crawley looks to duck under but gets hit on the shoulder. Rabada gives a look after that delivery to Zak. Rabada will be looking to pepper Crawley with some more short stuff as Zak is clearly struggling against the bouncers.
Length ball on off, Crawley defends it out.
Good length ball on off nipping away. Sibley attempts to defend it but takes the outside edge and goes towards gully.
Good length on off, Dominic this time solidly blocks it out to cover.
Full delivery on off, moving away. Sibley defends it to point.
Fuller one outside off, this one is coming in. Sibley shoulders arms to this one.

Appeal by South Africa but turned down! Height maybe? Good length ball around off, swinging in. Sibley shoulders arms but gets hit on the thigh pad. Philander appeals but the umpire Kumar Dharmasena shakes his head, signalling height as the issue. South Africa did not even consider going for the review.
Well fielded! Fuller one outside off, Sibley drives this beautifully towards mid off. Maharaj comes across and slides to make an excellent stop.
Another nasty one! Back of a length ball on middle, Zak attempts to flick this one but it goes on to hit the thigh pad. Rabada has been all over Crawley so far in this opening session.
Short of a length ball on middle, Crawley hops and defends it to short leg.
FOUR! Very full delivery down the leg side, Crawley just helps it on its way to the fine leg region for a boundary.
On middle, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length ball on off, Sibley stands tall and blocks it out to point.
Length ball on middle, Sibley solidly pushes it back to mid on.
Full delivery outside off, Crawley leaves this ball alone.
Good length ball on the fourth stump line, Zak does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Crawley flicks it to mid-wicket.
Fullish delivery outside off, nipping in a little. Zak lets it through to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to this one.

FOUR! Good stuff from Crawley. He hasn't had it easy out there but this will give him some confidence. Philander dishes out a full delivery on middle, Zak whips it to the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Brilliant from Rabada! Back of a length ball in the channel of uncertainty. Sibley looks to defend off the back foot but it whizzes past the bat and into the mitts of the keeper.
Fullish outside off, Sibley lets it go to the keeper.
Good length on middle and leg, Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length on middle, Sibley works it to square leg for nothing.
On off, Sibley defends it off the back foot to point.

EDGY FOUR! Anrich Nortje comes into the attack and induces an edge straightaway. Starts with a length ball around off, Crawley looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge which flies through the empty gully region and into the third man fence.
Full delivery outside off, Zak leaves it alone.
Back of a length delivery on off, Crawley rocks back and defends it out.

Excellent fielding! Short of a length ball on middle, Crawley pulls it away handsomely towards deep mid-wicket but Pretorius comes across from deep square leg and slides to collect it with just a single hand. Two taken.
BEATEN! Short of a length outside off, Zak looks to punch it off the back foot but fails to make any connection with it.
The batsman has driven it towards mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery outside off, Dominic lets the ball go to the keeper.
Fullish outside off, Sibley once again makes a leave to this one.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley works it to the leg side for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Excellent catch from Quinton de Kock and Rabada gets his reward for persistent bowling. Brilliant stuff! Fullish delivery outside off, Crawley looks to go for the cover drive without moving his feet. The bat turns a bit in his hand and the ball goes off the outside edge between first slip and the keeper. De Kock dives to his right and pouches it with both his hands in front of Rassie van der Dussen who was moving to his left. Rabada is ecstatic. Can they get another wicket before Lunch? Joe Denly walks out to bat at number 3, replacing the free-flowing Zak Crawley.
Good length delivery on off, Denly defends it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Sibley camps back and blocks it out to the leg side.
Fullish delivery on middle, Sibley works it to mid-wicket.
Snorker of a delivery from Nortje! Short of a length ball on middle, Sibley looks to defend but gets hit on the gloves and the ball lobs towards square leg. A single taken.
Length ball on middle, Denly looks to work it to the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Back of a length ball on off, Denly hops and defends it out.
On off, defended back to the bowler.
FOUR! Poor delivery from Rabada! Full delivery on the pads, Sibley will not miss out on those. He just flicks it towards the deep square leg region for a boundary.
Good length ball on off, Dominic defends it out to cover.
Full delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Sibley works it to square leg and crosses over for a single. The fielder has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Denly was in though.
Fullish delivery on off, Denly prods forward and defends it out.

FOUR! That is a beautiful way to get off the mark. Rabada dishes out a full delivery on off, Denly gets into position and creams the drive through mid off for a boundary. Nortje runs after it but fails to get there in the end.
Good length ball on the off pole line, worked towards the mid-wicket region for a single.
Length ball on off, left alone by Denly.
This time a length ball on the off pole line, the batter blocks it out.
Length ball on middle and off, Denly hops and works this one towards the leg side.
This time pushes the length ahead a bit does Nortje. Denly drives the ball towards mid on.
On the hips of Denly, he works the ball towards the man at square leg.
Pretorius starts with a length ball outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to it.

An appeal for LBW but it is turned down. On a length on middle, Sibley looks to flick but gets hit on the elbow and the ball goes onto the pads before rolling to the leg side. Pretorius appeals but nothing from the umpire. The Proteas think of a review but decide against it.
Good length delivery on middle, Sibley defends it out.
FOUR! That's not the place to bowl to Sibley. He is very strong there. Full delivery on middle, Sibley whips it through mid-wicket and the ball races into the fence.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley solidly blocks it out.
Fuller one on off, Denly pushes it back to Nortje.
OHH! Good length ball on middle, nipping in, Joe looks to flick it but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Full on middle, Denly pushes it to mid on.
Short of a length ball outside off, Denly sways away from it.
Back of a length on off, Denly defends it to cover and takes a quick single.
FOUR! This is poor, poor bowling from Nortje. Short of a length delivery on the pads, Sibley works it to the fine leg region for a boundary. The lead now moves to 94.

FOUR! Beautiful shot from Denly. Low full toss on middle, Denly whips it through mid-wicket and the ball goes into the fence. The Proteas are losing their lines and lengths out in the middle. 50 up for the visitors.
Denly defends this length ball on middle to the leg side.
Fullish delivery on off, Joe defends it off the front foot back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Denly works it to mid-wicket.
On off, defended solidly off the back foot by Denly.
Fullish delivery on off, Joe blocks it out onto the pitch.
Nortje dishes out a full ball on off, Sibley pushes it to mid off.
BEATEN! Nicely bowled! South Africa have to bowl more on this channel! Back of a length ball outside off, Sibley goes on his back foot to defend but gets squared up and misses it.
Short of a length ball on off, Sibley blocks it out to mid on.
Full delivery on off, Sibley defends it out.
BOUNCER! Nortje bowls this around middle, Sibley ducks under it.

Well well! What happened there? On a length on middle, Sibley looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge towards short leg. Sibley moves out of his crease and Pieter Malan at short leg collects the ball but does not throw it back. Sibley has to dive back in his crease.
Maharaj starts with a flighted ball on middle, Denly plays it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery on middle, pushed back to Maharaj.
On off, defended out by Denly.
Floated ball on off, Denly strides forward and defends it out to silly point.
Tosses this one up on middle, Joe blocks it out solidly.
Looped up ball on off, Denly blocks it to the off side.
Philander starts with a full ball on off, Sibley works it to the man at mid on.
Length ball on off, left alone by Dominic.
Another fullish ball on middle and off, Sibley works it towards the man at short mid-wicket.
First run of the session as Sibley works the ball in front of square towards the leg side and takes a single.
Length ball on off, defended back towards the bowler.

Almost carried that one! Elgar thought he was in the game there. Full ball on middle, Denly works it towards mid-wicket but does so a bit uppishly. The ball is in the air for a bit but falls just short of Elgar.
Spin on offer straightaway. Floated on the off pole line, it pitches and turns away from Sibley. Dominic defends solidly though.
Floated on off again, Sibley defends with the full face of the bat.
Outside off, Dominic plays this one towards the man at cover-point.
Sibley comes onto the front foot and pushes this ball towards cover. Looks for a single but not on offer.
Tossed up on off, Dominic has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Sibley has pushed that ball towards the off side. Second maiden in a row for Keshav Maharaj.
Length ball on off, Denly defends it towards the off side off the back foot.
This time a touch fuller, Denly prods forward and defends it.
Back of a length ball outside off, left alone by Denly.
Good length ball on the pads, on middle. Denly flicks it straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, defended back towards the bowler.
Fuller ball on off, worked down to the man at mid on.
Little bit of turn again for Maharaj as he floats this one on the off pole line. Sibley works it towards the leg side.
Single for Sibley and that brings up the 100-run lead for England. Floated on middle and leg, Sibley works this one towards the man at mid-wicket and takes a quick single to get to the other end.
Floated on off, defended towards the off side by Denly.
FOUR! Maharaj floats one on middle and off, Denly dances down the track and smashes this one over mid off for a boundary. Cries for a catch but no fielder stood a chance.
Tossed up on off, Denly pushes this one towards the off side.
Another one which is tossed up on off, Denly defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball on off, left alone by Sibley.
Fuller one on middle, driven down to the man at mid on.
Length ball on off, played towards point.
Bowled in the channel outside off, Sibley defends it back towards the bowler.
Outside off, left alone by Dominic.
Again Philander bowls one outside off, Sibley makes the leave.
Up and over! Floated ball on off, Denly strides forward and lifts this over the cover region. The fielder chases after it and cleans it up. The batters take three.
Loopy delivery on off, with some spin on it. Denly defends it towards point.
Full on middle, Sibley defends it back towards the bowler.
Flatter delivery on middle, worked to the leg side for a single.
Floats this one up on off, Sibley looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes on the bounce to Faf du Plessis at first slip.
EDGY FOUR! Just wide of Faf at first slip! Lucky, very lucky. Tossed up ball outside off, Sibley looks to drive it but edges it which goes just past the diving Faf at first slip and into the fence.
BEATEN! On a length outside off, Denly looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Full delivery on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
On a length on middle, Denly works it to the leg side.
Fullish outside off, Denly lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball on off, defended towards the off side.
This time on the hips, Denly works it towards the leg side. 5th maiden out of 8 overs for Philander.
FOUR! Full delivery down the leg side, Sibley just helps it fine down the leg side for a boundary.
Floated on the off side, Sibley pushes it towards mid off and races through for a single.
This time Denly pushes it towards cover and takes another quick single.
Tossed up on off, worked to the man at mid on.
Outside off, played to the man at point.
Another one on off, this time it is pushed to the man at cover-point. 6 runs off the over.
Full ball on middle and off, driven towards the man at cover.
Another one which is full in length, Denly pushes it back to Philander who fakes a shy at the striker's end. Trying to ignite a spark.
Full ball on the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Philander bowls another one, wicket-to-wicket. Denly defends it onto the pitch.
Outside off, Denly drives this towards cover but the man there to dive and gather the ball. 6 maidens out of 9 overs for Philander. Unbelievable consistency.
Maharaj comes over the wicket now, bowls a loopy delivery down the leg side, Sibley pads it away.
Floated on middle, blocked out by Sibley.
Down the leg side, padded away by Dominic again.
Tossed up on the pads, Sibley looks to flick but misses it to get hit on the pads. It lobs off to short leg. Looks like that is the plan.
Floated on middle, Sibley blocks it to mid-wicket.
Comes around the wicket does Maharaj now and bowls a flighted ball on off, Sibley prods forward and defends it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Denly lets it go to the keeper.

In the air... safe! Well fielded as well. Rabada dishes a good length delivery outside off, Denly drives but does so uppishly. It goes over cover and is racing into the fence. Maharaj hares after it and slides to make an excellent stop. Two taken. The umpire go upstairs to check whether it is a clean save and the replays show that Keshav has done really well.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On a length outside off, Denly punches it through covers and picks up a single.
Back of a length ball outside off, Sibley lets the ball go to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Pitched outside leg, Denly pads it away.
Another one which is pitched outside leg, this time Denly goes for a powerful sweep but misses.
Again outside the leg pole line, Denly pads it away.
Outside off this time, Denly blocks it out.
Last ball of the over and bowled down the leg side. Padded away by Denly to get through the over.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Fullish ball on off, pushed down to the man at mid on.
Another one outside off, left alone.
Rabada bowls a full ball on middle, Sibley drives this one straight down the ground but Rabada stops it with his boot and the ball deflects off it towards mid off.
Length ball on middle, blocked out off the back foot.
Another one on middle, Sibley goes on his toes and defends.
Floated down the leg side, Denly pads it away.
Flatter one on middle, Denly defends it to cover.
Looped up down the leg side, Denly prods forward and pads it away again.
Flighted ball on the pads, Denly looks to sweep it but hits the pads and rolls to square leg.
Fuller on middle and leg, Denly pushes it to point.
On middle and leg, blocked out to the bowler.

FOUR! Creams it! Full ball outside off, Sibley gets down on one knee and drives it in the gap in the cover region for a boundary. 50-run stand comes up with this beautiful stroke. England are effectively 124/1.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on middle, pushed to the man at mid on.

Little bit of indecision here between the batters but in the end no harm done. Good length ball on off, Sibley pushes it towards cover and sets off for a single. Denly is hesitant but obliges very late. The man at cover picks up the ball and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Replays roll in and show that even if he had hit, Denly was well in.
Denly goes onto the back foot and has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Back of a length ball on the body, Denly pushes it towards the off side.
Flatter delivery outside off, cut to point for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Denly has pushed this tossed up delivery towards wide mid off for a single.
Bowled outside off by Maharaj, left alone.
Sibley prods forward and defends this ball.
On middle and leg, Sibley flicks this one towards mid-wicket.
Rabada starts after the mini-break with a length ball outside off which is left alone by Denly.

Full ball on middle and off, Denly drives it down the ground. Rabada bends down and gets a hand to the ball, trying to deflect it onto the stumps at the non-striker's end but Sibley in the meantime gets back inside the crease.
Bouncer on middle and off, ducked under by Denly.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Back of a length ball on middle, pulled to square leg for a single by Denly.
Good length ball on middle, pushed down to mid on. Rabada conceding runs unlike Philander who has been super-consistent.
Floated on middle, Denly pushes it back to the bowler.
Loopy on middle, Joe works it to mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, Denly blocks it out.
Tossed up ball on the pads, Denly looks to sweep but gets hit on the pads. No harm done.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter one on off, Denly pushes it to silly point where Pieter Malan makes the stop.
Nortje starts with a ball outside off, Sibley plays it towards point and takes a run.
Length ball on the body, Denly pulls this one towards square leg for a couple.
On the pads of Denly, he looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The batters steal a leg bye as the ball rolls towards the leg side.
Bouncer on off, ducked under.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
On the pads, flicked towards the leg side for nothing.
Maharaj comes over the wicket and bowls down the leg side. Denly sweeps but the man at deep backward square leg stops it and the batters take a run.
On the pads again, flicked towards square leg for one.
Pitched outside leg, padded away.

Another one which is pitched outside leg, Denly sweeps it towards backward square leg for one. It is getting difficult to figure out what the plan is here by the Proteas. They are just conceding runs at the moment without posing any danger.
Maharaj comes around the wicket and bowls one outside off now. Sibley leaves it alone comfortably.
Floated nearer to the off pole now, Sibley prods forward and defends.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball on the body, defended towards the leg side.
Denly rocks back and defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length ball on middle, Denly goes back and pulls towards mid-wicket for a single.
On off, defended towards the off side by Sibley. The contest has become very stagnant right now with no side coming out with a positive approach.
Full ball on middle, pushed down to the man at mid on. End of another over of which only 1 run came.
Looped up ball down the leg side, Denly looks to sweep but it goes off his pads and towards short fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Flatter one on off, Sibley pushes it to cover.
FOUR! Finally, finally, we see a boundary. Flatter one outside off, Sibley waits for it and punches it through the covers for a boundary.
Tosses this one up on middle, Sibley drives it past the diving Maharaj down to long on for a single.
Looped up ball on middle and leg, Denly works it to mid-wicket.
On off, pushed to mid off.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and leg, Sibley ducks under it.
Back of a length on middle, Sibley tucks it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
BOUNCER! Nortje dishes this one around middle, Denly does well to duck under it.
Comes over the wicket does Nortje and bowls a length ball on off, Denly defends it to point.
Full delivery on off, Joe defends it to mid off.
Short of a length outside off, Denly punches it to deep point and takes a single.
Floated on the pads, Denly works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter one down the leg side, Denly pads it away.
Tossed up ball on the leg stump line with some extra bounce. Denly looks to pad it away but gets hit on the gloves. No run.
Down the leg side, Joe once again pads it away.
Short of a length delivery on middle, Denly pulls it to backward square leg and takes a single.
Maharaj comes around the wicket and bowls a flat one outside off, Sibley punches it to cover.

MISFIELD! Full delivery on middle, Denly pushes it towards mid on where Rabada allows the ball to pass through him and it is rolling towards the fence. By the time Rabada can recover and clean it up, the batters pick up a couple.
Very full down the leg side, Denly looks to flick it but misses it. De Kock dives to his left and makes the stop. Seems to have hurt himself in the process.
Short delivery on middle, pulled to mid-wicket.
Fullish on off, Denly pushes it to cover.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, we have seen a wicket fall. Brilliant delivery from Nortje. Another start from Denly and he has thrown his wicket away. It has been a trend lately from him. Short delivery on off, Denly looks to pull but it takes the top edge and goes towards fine leg. Pretorius runs forward and tumbles to take an excellent catch. A slow-going but an excellent partnership comes to an end. South Africa would hope that this opens up the floodgates and gives them a chance in this game.
Bouncer first up to Root. It is bowled around off, Root sways away from it.
Floated ball on the pads, Sibley looks to pad this one away but gets hit on the elbow area.
Flatter one on middle, Sibley defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, Dominic works it to square leg.
Floated on off, Sibley defends it to cover.
Loopy delivery on the pads spinning away, Sibley looks to defend off the front foot but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Flat one on off, pushed to mid off.
Short delivery down the leg side, Root pulls it to backward square leg and a single is taken.
Fullish on middle and leg, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length ball on off, Sibley stands tall and blocks it to the off side.
Comes around the wicket and dishes a short ball around middle, Sibley hops and defends it out to short leg.
Short delivery on middle, Sibley works it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
Another short one on middle, Root pulls it wide of mid on and crosses over for a single.
FOUR! Time for some innovation! Maharaj bowls a full delivery on middle, Root goes on his knees and reverse sweeps the ball towards the third man region for a boundary.
BEATEN! Not this time says Maharaj. Floated ball down the leg side, Root looks to play the reverse sweep again but misses it and it goes on to hit Quinton de Kock on the chest.
On off, pushed to point and a single is taken.
Floated on middle, defended to short leg.
Floated on off, Sibley prods forward and defends it out.
Flatter one on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot. TEA ON DAY 3.
Rabada starts with a short delivery on middle, Root gets the first run of the session by pulling this to deep square leg.
Back of a length ball on middle, Sibley rocks on his back foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish ball outside off, Sibley lets the ball go to the keeper.
On middle, defended off the front foot towards mid-wicket.
Good length on off, Sibley defends it to cover.
On a length on middle, Dominic works it to mid-wicket.
Just short! Flatter one on off, pitching on the rough. Root plays it with soft hands and guides it to first slip. Luckily, it falls in front of Faf.
Looped up ball down the leg side, Root looks to sweep but misses it altogether.
Floated ball on the pads, Root looks to defend but hits the pads and rolls to the off side.
FOUR! This is poor bowling from Maharaj! Bowls a full one down the leg side, Root sweeps it past the keeper and into the fence.
Down the leg side, Root pads it away.
The batsman offers no stroke and gets hit on the pad.
FOUR! Nicely played from Sibley! Short of a length from Rabada! Sibley stands tall and punches it through the covers for a boundary. Two fielders chase after it but fail to get there. Moves to 48.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around off, Dominic sways away from it.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball outside off, Sibley pushes it to point off the back foot.

FIFTY! Maiden fifty for Sibley in Tests! It has been an excellent innings so far. He has got starts in his previous innings but failed to convert it into a big one. He finally has managed to convert one into a half ton. Can he convert this into a maiden ton as well? Good length ball on off, Sibley guides it through gully and picks up a couple.
Short ball outside off, Dominic sways away from it.
Floated ball on middle, Root plays the reverse sweep to deep point for a single.
Flatter one on off, Sibley pushes it to cover and takes a single.
Floated down the leg side, Root pads it away.
Quicker one on middle, Root defends it out onto the pitch.
Flighted ball down the leg side, Root looks to play the reverse sweep but gets an inside edge which goes towards first slip.
Down the leg side, Root looks to play the sweep it but misses it altogether.
Full delivery on off, pushed to cover.
Full delivery on middle, Sibley pushes it down to mid on.
On off, pushed to cover off the front foot.
EDGY FOUR! Sibley is riding his luck here! Fullish delivery on off, Sibley looks to defend with soft hands but it takes the outside edge and the ball goes through gully and into the fence.
FOUR! No luck this time! It is a proper cricketing shot! Overpitched delivery on middle and leg, Sibley flicks it through mid-wicket and collects a boundary.
On off, pushed towards mid off.
Flatter delivery down the leg side, Root looks to play then reverse sweep but then sees it is too wide and then lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish delivery on off, pushed to long off for a single.
Floated ball on the pads, Sibley pads it away.
Flatter delivery down the leg side, Sibley flicks to short leg for a single.
Loopy on of, pushed to cover.
Flighted on middle, root sweeps it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
Fuller ball on off, pushed to mid on.

Whoa! That hit the crack. Probably first time Pretorius has landed the ball there. It is just behind good length. It pitches and then shoots off. Root awkwardly defends as the ball hits the upper part of his bat.
Full delivery on off, Root pushes it to point.
On off, root comes forward and defends it out to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on off, Root blocks it out onto the pitch.
Good piece of fielding! Full delivery on middle, Root drives it straight back. Rassie van der Dussen who is standing at silly mid on dives to his left and stops it.

FOUR BYES! But was it? Flighted ball down the leg side, Root looks to pad it away but the ball misses his attempt. De Kock is blinded by the batsman and he cannot collect the ball and it rolls to the fine leg fence. Now, the umpire signals it four byes. Faf du Plessis is not happy as he tells the umpire brushed the pads and hence it should not be four byes but a dead ball. And replays confirm the same.
On the pads again, Sibley pads it away this time.
Around middle, Sibley goes back and punches it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller and on middle, it is driven towards covers for a single.
Padded away again as Maharaj's another attempt of extracting something off the rough fails.
On middle, it is turned towards mid-wicket for a single.
On a length on middle, Sibley works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket again.
Very full delivery on middle, Dominic gets his bat down in time and whips it to the leg side.
Good length ball on off, Sibley defends it to point.
Fullish on middle, whipped wide of mid on and a single is taken.
Root defends this good length ball on off to point.
Loopy delivery down the leg side, Sibley pads it away.
Down the leg side, Sibley has no problems in padding it away.

What has happened there? Luck is going Sibley's way at the moment. Floated ball on middle and leg, Sibley looks to flick but gets a leading edge towards point. Zubayr comes forward to collect but ball spins in front of him and goes past him. Two taken before Hamza can collect it and throw it back.
Looped up down the leg side, Sibley keeps on padding this one awy.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
FOUR BYES! Another one down the leg side. Sibley leaves it alone. Quinton de Kock fails to collect it and it goes past the diving first slip fielder and into the fence.
Landed on middle, Root works it behind square leg for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller one outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball on off, Dominic defends it to cover.
Full delivery on middel, Sibley pushes it past the silly mid on fielder and towards long on for a single.
Down the leg side, Root pads it away to the of side.

FOUR! Nicely played! What timing! Flater delivery on middle and leg, Root just pushes it though the mid-wicket region for a boundary. The fielder chases after it but fails to do so. 50-run partnership is also up between the two.
Floated on middle, flicked to the leg side for a single.
Fuller one down the leg side, padded away.
Maharaj comes around the wicket and bowls a full delivery on off, Sibley takes a stride forward and defends it out.
FOUR! Cut away beautifully. Short delivery outside off, Sibley rocks on his back foot and cuts it through the point region for the second boundary of the over. The lead  crosses 200.
Good length ball on off, Root defends it out.
Full delivery on middle, Joe defends it back to the bowler.
On a length on middle, Root solidly defends it out to silly mid on.
On middle, solidly blocked.
Very full delivery on middle, Root flicks this to deep square leg and takes a single.
On a length on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot.
Flatter delivery on the pads, Root looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Floated down the leg side, Root lunges forward and defends it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! This line is basically not working for Maharaj. Poor, poor stuff. Fuller one down the leg side, Root goes on his knees and paddle sweeps it through fine leg for a boundary.
Flatter delivery on middle, Root works it to the leg side for a single.
On middle, defended out by Sibley.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.

Good length ball on off, Root pushes it back to the bowler. Pretorius gets down to stop the ball but it touches his fingers and goes past the stumps at the non-striker's end. Sibley was backing up and he quickly tried to get in seeing the ball coming towards the stumps. However, it does not hit the stumps and goes behind. The mid off fielder fields it.
Full and on the middle, it is flicked nicely but the mid-wicket fielder makes a sharp stop.
Full delivery on middle, Root drives it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, with some extra bounce, Root defends it to cover.
On middle, pushed to silly mid on.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on the pads, Sibley works it to deep square leg for a single.
Full delivery on off, Root guides it towards point and a single is pinched before Malan cuts it off.
Fullish delivery outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.

An appeal for LBW turned down. Good length ball on middle and leg, Sibley looks to work it to the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad. Vernon appeals but the umpire shakes his head. It was probably going too high.

Risky leave! That was very close. Philander dishes a length ball around off, moving in. Sibley does not expect that and lets it go. Luckily for Sibley, the ball just goes over the off stump and into the keeper's gloves.
On off, defended to the bowler.
Full on off, pushed to mid off.
Full on middle, Root drives it straight back. Van der Dussen dives to his left and stops it.

FOUR! Brilliant shot from Root! He is looking in good touch here. Full delivery outside off, Root lunges forward and drives it through covers. Maharaj hares after it and slides to stop it but fails to do so.
On off, defended to point.
Good length delivery on off, Root pushes it to cover and calls Sibley for a quick single.
On a length on off, with extra bounce. Sibley defends it to point.
Philander dishes out a good length ball on off, Root defends it to cover.
Full delivery on middle, Root drives but Vernon makes a half stop with his right hand. The ball rolls to mid on but no run taken.
Fullish on middle, Root blocks it out.
On off, pushed to point off the front foot.
On a length on middle, Root works it to mid-wicket and takes a single. Maharaj slides and collects the ball.
Fullish on middle, Sibley defends it out.
Full delivery on off, Root pushes it to cover.
On middle, Root defends it out to silly mid on.

FOUR! This is not good bowling from Pretorius. Giving easy runs to England. Full toss on middle and leg, Root flicks it beautifully towards the fine leg region for a boundary. Rabada hares after it but does not get there in time.
Good length delivery on off, Root defends it towards point for a single.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Length ball on off, Dominic defends it to the of side off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Root defends it to cover.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Root works it to the leg side.
On a length on off, Root guides it to point.
Fullish on middle, pushed to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Joe pushes it to the point fielder.
Short of a length on off, Root pushes it through covers and picks up a couple before the fielder can clean it running from point. 1000 runs for Root against the Proteas in Tests.
FOUR! Starts with a horrendous delivery! Flatter delivery outside off, Sibley rocks on his back foot an punches it through the cover region for a boundary.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Floated on middle, Sibley works it to mid on.
Flatter one on off, Sibley pushed to cover.
Loopy delivery on middle, Sibley looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge towards square leg.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Good length ball outside off, Root guides it to gully for nothing.
On a length on off, Root hops and defends it out.
Back of a length on off, Root pushes it to deep cover and crosses over for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Sibley works it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length around middle and leg, Sibley looks to work it to the leg side. It hits his gloves and rolls onto the pitch.
Good length on off, Dominic pushes it to point and takes a single.
On middle, Sibley defends it off the front foot to square leg.
Full delivery on middle, Sibley pushes it back to Maharaj.
Looped up ball on off, Sibley defends it to cover.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler off the front foot.
Flighted on middle and leg, Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket.
On off, defended out. Another maiden over from Maharaj.
Full delivery on off, keeping a little low, Root gets his bat down in time and defends it to mid off.
On a length on off, Root defends it to cover and calls Sibley for a single.
Back of a length on off, Sibley hops and defends it to the leg side.
Fullish on middle, worked to mid-wicket.

On a length on middle, Sibley pushes it back past the bowler. He waits for the ball to go past Nortje and then takes a single. The fielder from mid on collects it and has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
Fuller one on off, Root pushes it to mid off.
Full on middle and leg, worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, pushed to the bowler.
Floated on off, Sibley pushes it through covers and picks up a couple before the fielder can come across and clean it up.
Looped up on middle, flicked to the leg side.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated on middle, Sibley pushes it back to the bowler.
Comes around the wicket and bowls a length ball on middle, Root guides it to gully.
Fullish delivery on middle, Root works it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length down the leg side, Root pulls it to square leg and takes a single before Elgar cleans it up.

FOUR BYES! That is poor bowling! Not going to affect Sibley at all. Short of a length ball down the leg side. Sibley leaves it alone and Quinton jumps and tries to collect but fails to do so. It goes into the fence for four byes.
FOUR! What a shot that one from Sibley! Short of a length ball on middle and leg, Sibley hops and whips it towards the deep mid-wicket region for a boundary.
On middle, defended off the front foot by Sibley.
Floated on off, Root paddle sweeps it to fine leg for a couple. Rabada comes across from deep square leg and cleans it up.

FOUR! FIFTY! 46th for him in Tests. Brillaint innings from the skipper. He has played beautifully in this innings. From the first ball, he has looked very comfortable. Maharaj bowls a full delivery on middle, Root sweeps it through the deep square leg region for a boundary. 100-run stand is also up between the two.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Short of a length on off, Root cuts but finds the point fielder.
Driven through mid off by the batsman. One run added to the total. 250 is now the lead for England.
Floated on middle, Sibley plays it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Root flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and leg, Sibley ducks under it
Short of a length on middle, Sibley hops and works it to short leg.
Short of a length ball on middle, Sibley tucks it to mid-wicket and picks up another single.
Another short one on middle, Root pulls it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
BOUNCER! It is bowled down the leg side, Sibley lets it be.
Good length ball on off, Root guides it towards gully. He wants the run but as he sees the fielder diving to collect, he decides against it.
Short of a length ball outside off, Root punches it through point and calls Sibley for a couple.
Full delivery on off, Root defends it to the off side.
On a length on off, Root pushes it to deep cover and takes a single.
Full delivery outside off, Sibley pushes it past the point fielder and picks up another couple.
On a length on off, Dominic defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish delivery on middle, Root reverse sweeps it to deep cover and picks up a couple.
On middle, defended out off the front foot by Root.
Floated ball down the leg side, Root sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Fuller one on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, Sibley leaves it alone. Quinton de Kock fails to collect it cleanly and the ball rolls to fine leg. A bye taken.
Full ball on middle and leg, Root reverse sweeps it towards deep point for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Root defends it back to the bowler.
On off, defended off the front foot by Joe.
Full delivery on middle, Root works this past silly mid on. No run.

OUT! CAUGHT! Root cannot believe it. Pretorius does the trick. Good length ball on off, hitting a crack around the off stump. It moves away a little. Root looks to defend it of the front foot but gets a thick outside edge which goes towards first slip. Faf du Plessis moves to his right and takes a simple catch. End of an excellent innings from Joe Root but surely he will feel that he missed out on a century. That ends a match-defining partnership. Will this be a match-winning one too? Is a nightwatchman coming?
Fullish and around off, Bess gets behind the line of it and defends it.

That took off! Probably due to one of those cracks. Pretorius bowls it on a length outside off, it pitches and takes off. De Kock moves to his left to collect the ball but it hits his fingers and goes behind. A bye stolen by the batters.
Full delivery on middle, Bess defends it out off the front foot.
Bangs this one short and angles it in. Well, that's all right but the line is not right as it lands on middle and leg and goes down the leg side as Bess ducks under it easily.
On off, a solid defensive stroke from Bess now.
That's a good leave! A good length ball angled into the right-hander. Bess covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Shortish ball around middle, Bess this time stands tall and taps it onto the pitch.

OUT! Caught down the leg side and the nightwatchman cannot see off the day for England. Brilliant ball this one from Nortje. Bends his back and bowls a bouncer on middle and leg. Bess looks to fend it away but misses. De Kock behind the wicket pouches the ball and makes a loud appeal along with the slip cordon and the bowler. Not out says the umpire. Now, should South Africa opt for the review against the nightwatchman with just a minute left for Stumps? Well, Nortje, the bowler himself is not sure. Du Plessis and de Kock is confident though and the skipper eventually signals the 'T'. Interesting. Let's see what the replays show. Front foot is alright. Let's go to the business end now. Here comes Ultra Edge. Wow, a deflection off the gloves, detects the Ultra Edge. The umpire has to change his decision. Out it is and a very good review from South Africa. AND WITH IT, STUMPS ON DAY 3 AS WELL.
Pretorius starts with a fuller delivery around off, Sibley starts his innings with a solid front foot defense.
Good length ball outside off, Sibley is in no hurry to score the first runs of the day and leaves it alone.
Dwaine hits the deck hard around off, Sibley defends it with a straight bat.
Good length ball around off, Dominic defends it towards cover off his back foot.
Pretorius goes short for the first time. Sibley keeps his eyes on the ball and sways away from it.
Pretorius finishes the over with a length delivery outside off. DS leaves it alone. Maiden to start the day.
Flighted delivery on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
Ben is off the mark! Tossed up around off, Stokes gets down on one knee and sweeps it towards fine leg for a single.
On the pads, Sibley tickles it fine down the leg side but the man at fine leg is inside so Dominic does not get a single he is looking for.
On the pads, Sibley leaves it alone. It kisses his pad and goes past the man at leg slip. Runs won't be counted as DS did not offer any shot.
Another one down the leg side, Sibley leaves it alone.
Floated on off, Sibley defends it to get through the over.
Good length ball on off, Stokes defends it off the back foot.
On the pads, Stokes looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Length delivery on off, BS defends it with a straight bat.
Pretorius targets the stumps. Ben blocks it with calmness.
Back of a length around off, Stokes punches it but to mid off.
FOUR! That was going to the fence as soon as he hit it. Good length ball outside off, Stokes pulls it using the power of his bottom hand and the ball races away to the mid-wicket fence.
On the pads from around the wicket. Sibley pads it away.
Once again on the pads, Sibley taps it onto the ground wide of leg slips.
On the pads and once again Sibley pads it away.
Floated on the pads, Sibley flicks it fine down the leg side and gets a couple. First runs off the day for Dominic.
On the pads, Sibley once again offers no stroke and pads it away.
Tossed up on off, Sibley blocks it.
SIX! Right out of the meat of the bat. That was six the moment he hit that. Full on off, Stokes maintains his balance and smashes it straight over Pretorius' head for a biggie.

FOUR! Innovative from Stokes and he has connected it really well. 14 for Ben Stokes from Pretorius' last 3 deliveries. Dwaine pulls his length back and bowls it on off and middle. Stokes reverse sweeps it over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Now Ben gets back into Test mode and blocks this off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Stokes defends it off his front foot.
On a length on middle, BS glances it to mid-wicket.
Length delivery on middle, Stokes punches it wide of mid-wicket and gets a single to keep the strike.
Floated on off, Stokes paddle sweeps it fine down the leg side for a brace.
SIX! Stokes has demolished that ball. Floated around off, Ben gets down on one knee and smothers the ball well over the mid-wicket fence for a monstrous biggie. Ben in T20 mode here.
Around the pads, Stokes tucks it through mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Tossed up on the rough outside off. Stokes goes for another slog sweep but the ball turns off the rough and hits Stokes on his arm.
Once again it turns off the rough and Ben is lucky to survive that. It pitches outside off and turns in off the rough. Stokes comes across and looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Floated on off, Stokes defends it to get through the over.
Philander starts with a fuller one on middle, Sibley gets on his front foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Short of a length outside off, Sibley shoulders arms to this one.
Fullish outside off, moving away, Dominic lets it through to the keeper.
On off, defended off the front foot to cover.
Length ball on middle, DS blocks it out onto the pitch.
On a length outside off, swinging away from the batsman. Sibley lets it go to the keeper to see off the over. A maiden from Philander on his return.
Flatter one on middle, Stokes pushes it down to long on for a single.
Floated outside off, Sibley leaves it alone.
Full on off, Dominic plays it back to Maharaj off the front foot.
BEATEN! Nicely bowled! Flatter one outside off, Sibley looks to push off the back foot but misses it completely.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Loopy on off, Sibley lunges and pushes it down to mid on.
Goes for the attacking option! Fullish delivery on middle, Stokes dances down the track and looks to heave it away but gets an inside edge which goes deep mid-wicket. a single taken.
Fullish on off, Sibley pushes it wide of mid off for a single.

FOUR! Beautiful shot! It is not a bad ball from Philander though. Low full toss on middle, Stokes whips it towards deep square leg. Elgar runs across from deep mid-wicket, dives to stop but fails to do so. It rolls into the fence.
Length ball outside off, Stokes looks to drive but gets a top edge. Luckily for him, it lands safely and goes towards deep cover. Two taken. The lead goes past 300.
FOUR! Stokes is latching onto Philander here. Short delivery outside off, Stokes stands tall and slams it through backward point for a boundary.
Short of a length outside off, Ben comes down the track and looks to cut but it takes the bottom edge and goes towards the keeper.
Floated on off, Sibley gets on his front foot and defends it.
Slightly shorter on off, Dominic defends it off the back foot.
Now goes around off, DS defends it towards cover-point.
Maharaj comes over the wicket and bowls on the pads. Sibley glances it through mid-wicket and gets a couple to get into the nervous 90s.
Darts on the pads, Sibley pads it away.
On the pads, Sibley defends it to get through the over.
Rabada starts with a length ball on middle, Stokes defends it off the back foot to mid-wicket.

TOP EDGE BUT SAFE! Luck favouring Stokes here! Short of a length ball on middle, Stokes looks to pull it but it goes off the top edge. The fine leg fielder is running ahead but stops as he sees Quinton de Kock  signaling that it is his catch. De Kock dives but fails to get any hand on it as well.
