There is a lot of breeze blowing around the ground and that may have taken it away from the keeper.
FOUR! Brilliant shot from Stokes! He is on a rampage here. Full toss on middle, Stokes hammers it over the mid-wicket region for a boundary.

Short of a length ball on middle, Stokes pulls it to deep square leg for a single. 50-run stand is also up between the two. This has been an attacking stand especially Stokes. They are going after the bowlers and are batting South Africa out of the game.

FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Sibley drives it through covers and is racing away to the fence. Dean Elgar runs across from deep cover and slides to make a stop. The umpire goes in to check whether it is a clean save but Elgar's leg has touched the ropes. England have crossed their first innings score and that too with six wickets in hand.
On a length on middle, Dominic defends it out. 11 from Rabada's first over on Day 4.
Flatter one this time, turning into the left-hander. Stokes tucks it towards square leg for a single.
On the pads, it is padded away by Sibley.
On the leg pole again, an easy flicked single towards square leg for Sibley.
Outside off on a fuller length, Stokes reverse sweeps it to deep point. A couple of easy runs for Stokes as Rabada from sweeper cover makes a sliding stop.
Full and on the pads of Stokes, he easily works it towards mid-wicket for a single. Maharaj has conceded 100 runs without picking a wicket now in this innings.
Another ball has been padded away by Sibley.

FIFTY! 21st Test fifty for Stokes. He has been positive since he came out to bat and has got to the milestone in just 34 balls. He gets there by pulling this short delivery to fine leg and taking a single. He definitely loves playing at this ground.
On a length on middle, Sibley defends it out to mid off.
Good length delivery on off, Dominic defends it to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Sibley looks to flick but gets a leading edge which rolls towards the off side.
Outside off, left alone by Dominic.

EDGY FOUR! Moves to 99 with a lucky boundary. Good length delivery on off, Sibley attempts to defend but gets squared up. It takes the outside edge and goes between the gully and the second slip fielders for a boundary.
Flatter delivery outside off, Stokes punches it through covers and collects a couple before the fielder comes across and clean it up.
On off, pushed down to long on for a single.
Flatter one down the leg side, Sibley is in no hurry to get to his hundred as he pads this away.
Down the leg side, padded away. Faf at leg slip dives to his right and cleans it up.

FOUR! CENTURY! Maiden Test ton for Dominic Sibley! A moment he, his family and all his friends will cheer and relish for the rest of his life. What a gem of a knock this has been from Sibley. Tossed up on the pads, Sibley gets down on one knee and sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary to reach the milestone. All the English fans and his teammates are on their feet applauding the efforts of this young man. He removes his helmet, raises it along with his bat and has a huge smile on his face. He deserves all the applaud he is getting as he has put his side in a commendable position in this game.
Fullish down the leg side, Sibley calmly pads this one away.
Fullish delivery on off, Stokes pushes it down to long off for a single.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Dominic looks to play at it first but then decides to leave the ball alone.
Edged but short! Good length ball on off, with some extra bounce. Sibley looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes on one bounce to gully.
On a length on middle, Sibley works it to deep square leg and takes a run.
Short delivery on off, Stokes punches it straight past the bowler and calls Sibley for a couple but decides against it as the long off fielder comes across quickly and cleans it up.
Full delivery outside off, Sibley leaves the ball alone.
PLAY AND A MISS! Misses out! Maharaj tosses this one up, landing it on the rough outside off and keeping a little low. Stokes looks to msweep but fails to get any bat on it.
FOUR! Bisects the two fielders perfectly. Short delivery this time on middle, Stokes pulls it in front of square and bisects the two fielders and goes into the fence.
SIX! Bang! That is hit a long way. Stokes is on fire at the moment. Flighted ball on middle, Stokes dances down the track and hammers it over the bowler's head for a biggie.

FOUR! Some innovation time from Ben! Brilliant. Floated ball on middle, Stokes plays the reverse sweep towards the deep point region for a boundary. 14 already from the over. Are England looking to declare soon?
Low full toss on middle, Stokes comes down and pushes it down to long on for a single.
Floated ball down the leg side, Sibley pads this one away.
Swing and a miss! A good length ball outside off, Stokes looks to tonk it over long off but misses.
Short and outside off, Stokes slaps it to sweeper cover for a single.
Good length ball on off, pushed to sweeper cover by Sibley this time.
Back of a length ball on off, Stokes pulls it to long on for a single.
In the channel outside off, Sibley is not affected from Stokes hammering from the other end as he calmly lets the ball go to the keeper.
Bumper on middle. Sibley easily ducks under it.

OUT! CAUGHT! An excellent hand from Ben Stokes comes to an end.  He has taken England to a very healthy lead in very quick time. He was putting on a show out there and was on his way to a quickfire century but it has been cut short. Maharaj who has had a torrid time with the ball finally has something to cheer about. Floated delivery around off, Stokes once again goes for the big slog sweep. He does not connect it well and the bat also turns in his hand. It goes to the right of long on. Rassie van der Dussen moves on that side and takes a good catch. It looked easy but it was not an easy one to take as the ball was hit with power and it was rushing onto him. Stokes walks out to a standing ovation from the crowd. Finally the hosts have something to smile about this morning but is it too late already?
Floated on middle, Pope defends it to mid-wicket.
On middle, Pope reverse sweeps it to deep cover for a single.
Flatter one on middle and leg, Sibley works it to the leg side for a single.
Fullish down the leg side, Pope pads this one away.

Looped up ball down the leg side, Pope flicks it to square leg where Rabada misfields and allows the ball to go towards the deep. Two taken before Philander comes across from fine leg and collects it.
Back of a length ball on off, Pope defends it out off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Pope guides it through gully and takes a single. He wants the second but it is not there as the fielder gets to it quickly.
On middle, worked to mid-wicket and takes a single.
On a length on off, Pope pushes it to cover.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Pope fails to repeat his heroics from the first innings! Two quick wickets for South Africa and this might help them to build some much-needed momentum here. Good length ball outside off, it keeps a bit low off the deck. Pope, who is a good off side player, looks to play it on the off side but fails to go fully with a horizontal bat. He ends up playing a shot with a half-vertical and a half-horizontal bat. He ends up getting an inside edge and the ball goes onto uproot the leg pole. England lead by 360. South Africa will now look to wrap it up under 400!
On middle, Buttler works it to the leg side for a single.
Fuller ball the pads, Buttler looks to paddle sweep it but misses.
Flatter one around off, it is defended.
Full and on the pads again, Buttler misses the sweep again. The ball hits the pads and rolls towards square leg. A leg bye taken.
Flatter one on middle, Sibley easily nudges it to fine leg for a single.
Outside off, pushed to mid off.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

Nortje starts his spell with a fuller ball around off, Sibley pushes it towards point and takes off for a quick single. The point fielder throws the ball at the non-striker's end after picking the ball quickly but he misses. Would not have mattered though as Sibley was in.
Around off on a shortish length. Blocked.

SIX! Wow! Just the extension of the arms and it flies over long off. Brilliant timing. Nortje overpitches it outside off, Buttler gets to the pitch of the ball and meets the ball on the full nicely. He just non-nonchalantly lofts it over long off for a biggie.
Shortish around off, tapped through point for a single.
WIDE! For height it is. An effort ball from Nortje as he bends his back and bowls a short of length ball outside off. Sibley lets it be as it goes well over his head.
On the pads, Sibley flicks towards mid-wicket and thinks for a single but the fielder there makes a sliding stop.
Landed around off, pushed towards point.
Down the leg side. No spin at all. Buttler looks to flick but misses.
Flatter one on the pads, worked behind square leg for a run.

SIX! Massive! Enough of blocking from Sibley as he gets into the zone now. A flighted ball in the slot of Sibley. He gets down on one knee and mows it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie. First one of his innings.
Flatter one on off, Sibley goes back to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Superb placement. Now a fuller ball from Maharaj down the leg side, Sibley sweeps it towards fine leg. There's no protection in the deep and the ball rolls to the fence. Easy runs these.
On the pads, Sibley this time pads it away.
Good length ball around off, it is defended.
SIX! Hammered! Second biggie off Buttler's bat now. A back of a length ball on off, Buttler goes on the back foot and slams it sailing over the deep square leg fence for half a dozen more
Shortish and outside off, Buttler taps it through point for a couple of runs.
Good length ball around off, driven through covers and another easy couple for Buttler.
Another couple and this brings up the 350 for England. A back of a length ball on middle, Buttler pulls it wide of the deep square leg fielder and runs an easy two.
Short again, pulled again. This time the deep square leg fielder does well to stop the ball with a slide. But he cannot stop another couple of runs for Buttler.
Very full delivery down the leg side, Sibley looks to flick but misses it completely.
Floated on the pads, Sibley goes on his front foot and defends it out.
Almost! That is close! Very full delivery down the leg side, Sibley looks to sweep but misses. It almost brushes the leg stump and goes to the keeper. Sibley tumbles after that shot.
On the pads, flicked to the leg side.
FOUR! Nice touch! Floated on the pads, Sibley tucks it nicely past the diving short fine leg fielder and into the fence. England's lead moves past 400.
Down the leg side, padded away by Sibley.

OUT! CAUGHT! Buttler tries an innovative shot but fails! No excitement shown by the Proteas as they know that they have backs to the wall. Good length ball on off, Buttler tries to play the scoop shot but it takes the gloves and goes to the keeper who collects with utmost ease. Buttler starts walking without even the umpire raising his finger. Buttler goes but not before playing a very handy cameo.
Good length ball on off, Curran pushes it to deep cover to get off the mark.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around off, Sibley sway away from it.
On off, pushed to cover and collects a single.
FOUR BYES! This is poor bowling! Giving easy runs to England. A bouncer around middle, very high though. Curran ducks under it. De Kock jumps to collect but it goes over and into the fence.
Much better from Nortje! Short ball around off, Sam sways away from it. End of a successful over from Nortje.
Flighted on the pads, Sibley tucks it to square leg and takes a quick single.
FOUR! Sam Curran joins the party! That is some shot from Curran. Maharaj dishes a half volley outside off, Curran leans forward and slams it through the cover region for a boundary.
Flatter one on middle, Sam pushes it back to the bowler.
On middle, worked to square leg.
Tossed up on middle, flicked to the leg side for a single.
Floated on off, Sibley defends it out.
FOUR! Pulled away handsomely! Short of a length ball on middle, Curran pulls it through deep square leg for a boundary. Second one for him in this innings.

OUCH! That mush have hurt! Short delivery on middle and leg, Curran looks to fend it away awkwardly but gets hit on the gloves. The ball lobs off towards the leg side. England will hope that Curran is not hurt badly as it is his bowling hand.
On middle, defended off the back foot to the bowler.
Short of a length outside off, Curran punches it towards the deep point region. The fielder from deep cover comes across, slides and stops the ball. The batters take two.
Full delivery on off, Curran plays it towards long on. Rabada comes across from long on quickly but does not collect cleanly. Only a single though.
Full on off, Dominic defends it off the front foot. LUNCH ON DAY 4.
Beaten! A flatter ball outside off, Curran pokes at it to get beaten.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! Caught! South Africa strike in the first over of the second session itself. Not the best of balls from Maharaj and he knows he is lucky to get a wicket of this delivery. A drag down on middle, Curran goes on his back foot and looks to pull it over mid-wicket. He cannot get under it and he is unable to get the desired elevation. It goes towards short mid-wicket where Zubayr Hamza takes a good catch, low to the ground. Now can South Africa bowl England out under 450?
Around the pads, Broad paddles it behind square on the leg side.
Floated on middle and leg, Broad looks to defend but the ball goes away down the leg side.

Good fielding from the substitute fielder, Keegan Petersen. Floated on leg, Broad gets down on one knee and sweeps it to the left of backward square leg. Petersen there dives to that side and saves runs for his side.
Back of a length on off, Sibley defends it off the back foot.
Full on off, Sibley looks to push it straight but it goes off the outer half of his bat through cover-point for a single. First run of the session for England and Sibley.
A big cheer from the English fans as Broad gets off the mark. Back of a length on middle, Broad hops up and dabs it to the off side and scampers to the other end.
Full on off, Sibley pushes it to mid on.
Full on off, Dominic pushes it to mid on.
Good length delivery outside off, Sibley defends it towards point.
FOUR! Very well played. Floated out off, Broad premeditates the sweep and hits it fine down the leg side. Elgar gives it a chase but gives up halfway as he knows he has no chance reaching that.
Flatter on off, Broad defends it out to the slip cordon. He wants the single but is sent back.
PLAY AND A MISS! Floated on off, Stuart looks to sweep but fails to get any bat on it.
BEATEN! Flatter one outside off, Broad looks to play it nice and fine on the off side but missed it altogether.
Tossed up ball around off, Broad looks to sweep but gets hit on the pads. There is a slight appeal for LBW but not given by the umpire.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
Full on off, Sibley pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on middle, Dominic works it to mid-wicket. Stokes signals to Sibley from the dressing room to attack a little more.
On a length outside off, Sibley guides it down to third man for a single.
BOUNCER! It is around middle and leg, Broad attempts the pull shot but fails to get any bat on it.
OHH! Short ball around the leg stump line, Broad looks to flick it but gets hit on the gloves and rolls to square leg. Broad wants the single but is not there.
Safe!!! Short of a length delivery on middle, Broad hops in an attempt to defend but gets hit on the splice of the bat. It lobs towards short leg but it falls just wide of him.
FOUR! Innovation from Sibley! Flighted ball on middle, Sibley reverse sweeps it through fine leg for a boundary. Dean Elgar chases after it from point but gives up the chase.
On middle and leg, Sibley sweeps it to backward square leg for a single.
Tossed up ball outside off, Broad bends and plays it down to long on for another run.
Fullish down the leg side, Sibley paddle sweeps but finds the short fine leg fielder.
On middle, Sibley plays the reverse sweep to cover and a single is taken.
Drops just short! Floated on middle, Broad gets on his knees to sweep this one but gets a top edge towards long on. The fielder from there comes after it but it falls way short. Two taken.
FOUR! Just the start South Africa needed. A very poor ball from Anderson to begin with. It is on the pads, Malan flicks it fine down the leg side and starts his innings with a boundary.
Once again it is around the pads with little to no movement. Malan glances it to mid-wicket.
Finally a real Anderson beauty! It is pitched just outside off and shapes away a tad. Malan shoulders arms to it and in the end it is a good leave as the ball misses the off pole by  a whisker.
Another good leave! This starts just outside off and comes in a bit. Pieter shoulders arms to it and this goes just over the off pole.
Good length ball outside off, Malan lets it carry to the keeper.
Solid leave to end the over. Good length ball on the fourth stump line, it jags back a bit but Malan is aware of his off pole and leaves it alone.
FOUR! Elgar is off the mark in style. Broad starts with an overpitched delivery way outside off. Elgar just uses the pace of the ball and guides it through point for a boundary.
Broad corrects his line and length and goes just outside off. Elgar shoulders arms to it.
On the pads, Elgar flicks it to the on side for a single.

NOT OUT! England lose their review! But what a decision from Kumar Dharmasena. This is top, top umpiring from the Sri Lankan. Brilliant ball from Broad. It is full and just around off. It jags back in viciously. Malan looks to defend but the ball hits the pad. The English players put in a huge appeal but the umpire turns it down. The English core of Broad, Stokes, Buttler and Root have a word and in the dying moments Root takes it upstairs. Replay rolls in and first it shows Broad is clean as his front foot is inside the crease. Time for Ultra Edge and ... it shows a spike as the ball goes past the bat. There is a feather of an inside edge. It looked plumb but tell you what, the umpire has produced a world class decision. Can't blame Root for taking it upstairs. England lose one of their two reviews. Malan survives, so South Africa are spared off a disastrous start.
Fuller ball on off, this time Malan comes forward and defends it.
Shortish around off, Malan taps it off the back foot towards point and takes a quick single.
Well played! Anderson dishes a good length ball outside off, Malan plays a back foot through covers. Denly chases after it and cleans it up. Two taken.
Length ball outside off, Pieter lets the ball through to the keeper.
Fullish ball on off, Malan defends it out to the off side.
On middle, Malan whips it to deep square leg and picks up a couple before the fielder can come across and clean it up.
Full delivery around off, Pieter defends it out off the front foot.
Back of a length ball outside off, Pieter shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, nipping away. Elgar does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
Fullish on middle and leg, Elgar whips it to mid-wicket.
On off, pushed to cover for nothing.
Fuller one on off, driven towards cover and takes a couple.
Broad dishes out a full ball on off, Elgar defends it towards cover and crosses over for a single.
Length ball on middle, Malan goes on his front foot and defends it back to Broad.
Good length ball on off, Elgar pushes it to cover and takes a single.

What happened there? England do not go for the review in the end. It was very close! Excellent umpiring from Paul Reiffel. Length ball around off, nipping into the batsman. Malan looks to defend off the front foot, there are two noises as the ball goes to the right of the keeper. Buttler behind the stumps dives on that side and takes it just above the ground. Buttler along with the other English players put in a huge appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Stokes, Buttler, Sibley and Root all gather and have a brief chat but  Anderson is not interested at all. He starts going back for his run up. In the end, they opt against the review. Probably the last review made them not go for it for this one. Very good decision in the end not to go for the review and Anderson not being excited is justified as Ultra Edge rolls in later on and it shows that the ball had kissed the front pad and not the bat before clipping the back leg and going to the keeper. Hawk Eye then comes in and it shows that the impact was outside off and the wicket was missing too. It would have been disastrous as the tourists would have lost both their reviews so early in this innings.
Good length ball angled into the right-hander. Malan covers his stumps and lets it be.
In the channel outside off, it is left alone.
Fullish and around off, Malan pushes it to point.
Another ball in the channel outside off, Malan makes another leave.
Good length ball on middle, Elgar blocks it off the back foot.
Slightly shortish length ball on middle, it is defended.
Landed around off, it is blocked.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards covers.
Another length ball angled into the batter by Broad by going wide of the crease. Elgar blocks it nicely.
Another short ball, it is defended.
Short of a length ball on off, Malan keeps it out.
Good length ball outside off, pushed towards point for a single.
Anderson angles this one away from the left-hander. Pitches it on a good length around leg and middle. Elgar blocks it towards point.

Nicely punched but excellent fielding. Slightly fuller on off, Elgar takes a step forward and punches it nicely towards mid off. Bess at that position dives to his left and makes a half stop and the ball is relayed towards mid on. Saved a certain boundary.
Good length ball on off, blocked towards point.

Quick single! A direct hit would've been interesting. Good length ball on middle, Elgar hops and works it towards mid-wicket. He takes off for the single but the ball goes towards the fielder quickly there. The fielder gets to the ball, picks it up and throws at the non-striker's end but misses.
Fuller around off, it is defended.
Outside off on a good length, left alone.
Back of a length ball on middle, Elgar pulls it behind square leg for a single.
Good length ball on off, it is defended by Malan.
Fuller and on off again, Malan pushes it back to the bowler.
That one shoot off. Probably off the cracks. It is landed outside off and rises sharply. Malan does well to defend.
Bess starts with a tossed up ball on middle, Elgar pushes it back to the bowler.

Flatter one on middle, Pieter stands back and defends it to short leg.

Good length ball on off, Pieter plays it to cover and single is pinched by the two batters.
Back of a length ball on middle, Elgar defends it off the back foot to square leg.
Fullish on middle, Malan works it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length on middle, Elgar pushes it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Beautifully played! Full delivery on middle and leg, Elgar flicks it towards mid on. Broad dives to his left but the ball bounces extra and goes past him. It races away to the fence.
On a length on off, Elgar looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and goes onto the pads. The ball rolls to the off side.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller one on the leg stump line, flicked to mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Malan blocks it out.
Flatter one on middle, Malan works it to the leg side.
On off, defended off the back foot by Malan.
Outside off, Pieter cuts it through point and collects an easy couple.
Fullish on middle, Pieter comes down and works it to mid on.
Floated on middle, Malan works it towards square leg and a single is taken.
Ohh, good fielding. Very full on middle, Malan flicks it but Pope at short leg does really well to stop it.
Length ball on off, PM defends it off his back foot.
Full and coming in with the angle on middle. Pieter defends it back to the bowler.
Anderson bowls it on a length outside off. There is little to no movement on this one. Malan does not go for the drive and lets it carry to the keeper.
Length ball outside off, Malan shoulders arms to it.
Anderson goes full and makes this one nip back in. Malan loses his top hand from the bat's grip but defends it well.
Floats this one up outside off, Elgar leaves it alone.
Loopy delivery on middle, Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
On off, pushed to cover off the front foot.
Flighted ball outside off, Elgar looks to drive but it takes the outside edge and goes to point.
On middle, worked to mid on.
Tossed up on off, Elgar prods forward and defends it to point.
Fullish on off, Malan defends it out to to the off side.
Good length ball on off, Pieter defends it to point.
On a length outside off, Malan makes a good leave to this one.
Fullish on middle, Malan works it to mid-wicket.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fullish outside off, left alone by Malan.
Full on off, pushed to short cover.
Flatter one on off, Elgar defends it to mid off.
Tossed up ball outside off, Dean shoulders arms to it.
Loopy delivery on middle, Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, defended out onto the pitch.
Floated on middle, worked through mid-wicket and collects a couple.
Curran starts with a full delivery outside off, Malan leaves it alone.
Fullish outside off, Malan prods forward and lets it go to the keeper.

That was close! Brilliant delivery! Full delivery outside off, moving in sharply. In the end, Malan lets it go to the keeper.
On off, defended out to the off side.
Curran bowls a full delivery on off, Pieter leans forward and blocks it out to cover.
Denly starts with a short one on middle, Elgar pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Short on middle, Denly pushes it to point.
Flighted fuller ball down the leg side, Malan looks to flick but gets hit on the pads and rolls towards short fine leg. A leg bye stolen.
Floated on off, landing it on the rough causing it to spin a little. Elgar looks to defend but it hits the handle and lobs to silly point.
Another one landing on the rough, Elgar looks to defend but hits the inside edge and onto the pads. No harm done though.
Flighted on middle, Elgar attempts the sweep shot but misses to get hit on the pads.
Outside off, left alone by Malan.
Good length ball outside off, Pieter lets the ball go to the keeper.
Fullish outside off, Malan makes a leave to this one.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller one outside off, swinging in, Malan shoulders arms to it.
No ball! Surprise, surprise a no ball has been called by an on-field umpire. Good length ball on off, Malan defends it out to the off side.
Fuller one on middle, worked to the leg side for a single.
Floated on middle and leg, Malan defends it out.
On off, Malan defends it to cover. Denly thinks that there was pad first and makes an appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head.
Flighted ball on off, Pieter prods forward and defends it out.

Flighted delivery on off, Elgar pushes it to cover.
On off, defended off the front foot to the off side.
Flatter one on middle, Dean defends it to the off side.
Outside off, driven to deep cover for single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Malan defends it out to the bowler. TEA ON DAY 4.
Denly starts with a flighted ball around off, landing in the rough. Elgar attempts to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Full outside off, Elgar pushes it towards deep cover and crosses over for a single.

Well, well that was close! Denly is making the ball talk. Floated ball outside off, landing in the rough. It bounces a little more and spins a little. Elgar looks to fend it away but it seems to have gone off the gloves and behind the keeper. Buttler dives behind to catch it but fails. Would not have mattered in the end if he had caught that as the replays show that it had hit the arm guard of Elgar.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. One run added to the total.

Full outside off, pushed towards cover and a couple is taken. 50-run stand is up between the two. Excellent partnership. This is what the hosts needed after being set a big total. Their job is not done yet and they would to bat for as long as possible.

BOUNCER! Wide given for height! It is bowled around middle and leg. Elgar ducks under it. It is wided for height.
Good length on middle, Dean works it to the leg side and a single is taken.
Good length on off, pushed to cover for nothing.

Luck for Elgar yet again. Floats this one up does Denly, on the rough. It spins a little. Elgar looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge and lobs towards square leg.
Full on middle, Elgar pushes it towards mid on and a single is taken.

Back of a length outside off, Pieter shoulders arms to this one.

EDGED BUT SAFE! On a length on off, Malan looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards second slip where the fielder collects it on the bounce.
On a length outside off, Malan shoulders arms to it.
Flighted on off, Elgar works it to the leg side for a single.
Floated on middle, Malan defends it back to the bowler.
Tosses this one outside off, Malan lets the ball go to the keeper.
Flighted on middle and leg, Malan comes forward and defends it to point.
Floated on middle, Malan works it to mid on and calls Elgar for a single.
Flatter one on middle, Elgar works it to short fine leg and another run is pinched by the two batters.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Elgar flicks it to mid-wicket.
On middle, worked to square leg.
On a length on off, Elgar stands tall and defends it to point.
On middle, Elgar pushes this down to mid on for another dot.
On off, defended off the back foot by Elgar.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Flatter delivery on middle, Malan moves inside his crease and punches it to cover.

FOUR! Poor bowling but this is what you will get from leg spinners. They tend to bowl bad balls from time to time. Full toss on middle, Malan just pushes this down past the mid on fielder and into the fence.
On the pads, Malan defends it out to short leg.
Short outside off, Malan punches it to the off side and takes a single.
Brave from Elgar. He got out going for a big shot in the previous ball but this time it is safe. Floated ball on off, Elgar dances down the track and heaves it over the mid off fielder. Two taken.

OUT! CAUGHT! Faintest of outside edges and Elgar has to go. Takes a review with him. Elgar cannot believe it as he believes that there was not bat on it. Flighted ball outside off, landing on the rough and spinning into the batsman. Elgar prods forward to defend but misses it. The English players appeal and after some thought, the umpire raises his finger. Elgar though is confident that he has not hit it at all so he goes for the review immediately. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows that there is a feather on it as it shows a small spike as the ball goes past the bat. Elgar is shocked as he trudges back to the pavilion. Can't blame Elgar for this as it was the slightest of feather which he might not have felt. He was looking very good out in the middle but needed to continue for his side. Finally England have got their way past the South African opener. Will this trigger a couple more before the end of day's play?
Good length ball on off, Malanm defends it from within his crease.
Full on middle, Malan pushes it to mid on.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Length ball outside off, Malan shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball outside off, Pieter strokes it towards point and gets to the other end.
Full on middle, Hamza flicks it right out of the middle of his bat but straight to mid-wicket.
On middle, defended out.
Flatter one on middle, Malan stands tall and defends it to point.
Floated on middle, Malan looks to defend but gets it off the inside half of the bat and goes towards the leg side for a single.
On off, defended out by the bowler.
Floated on middle, Zubayr defends it out,
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full outside off, Malan leaves the ball alone.
On a length outside off, bouncing a little more. Malan defends it to point and crosses over for a single.
Back of a length on off, Hamza hops and defends it out to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Hamza works it to square leg.
Length ball on off, Hamza defends it out to gully.
Nice looking shot but for no runs. Full delivery on off, Hamza drives it beautifully but finds the cover fielder.

Nice way to get off the mark! Flat one outside off, Hamza camps back and punches it through covers for a couple before the fielder can come across and clean it up.

Good length ball on middle, Zubayr solidly blocks it out.
EDGY FOUR! Frustrating for England. Fuller one on off, Hamza looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge and goes between the second slip and the gully fielders. The ball races to the fence.
Length ball on off, Hamza pushes it towards point and takes a single.
Good length on off, Pieter defends it to cover and wants a single but Hamza sends him back. Good decision in the end as there was no run there.
Flatter one on middle, Hamza defends it out.
Looped up on middle, Hamza looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge and rolls towards square leg.
On off, defended off the front foot.

BOUNCER! It is bowled around off, Malan sways away from it.

Back of a length ball outside off, Malan leaves this one alone.

Outside off, Malan moves inside his crease and punches the ball through the covers and picks up three before the fielder can come across and clean it up.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
BOUNCER! Broad dishes this one up around middle, Malan ducks under it.
Short ball outside off, with extra bounce. Malan lets this go to the keeper. Buttler jumps and collects it.
OHH! Full delivery on the pads, Malan looks to flick but it takes the leading edge and rolls towards mid off. Malan is annoyed with himself after playing that shot.
On a length outside off, Malan does not fiddle with it and lets it through to the keeper.
Fullish on off, Malan pushes it to cover off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Malan defends it towards the point region and a single is taken.
Floated on off, Malan comes down the track and looks to flick but it hits the edge and hits the boot. The ball rolls to the off side.
On middle, worked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Looped up ball on off, Hamza drives it to cover.
That's really well played from Hamza! Short of a length ball outside off, spinning in. Hamza gives himself room and punches it through covers for three. The fielder hares after it and makes the stop.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter one on middle, Pieter works it to deep mid-wicket and picks up a single.
No ball! Stokes has overstepped on his first ball. It is a big one at that. Starts with a short of a length ball on off, Malan defends it off the back foot to point.

FOUR BYES! Sharp turn on this one! Flighted delivery on middle, which spins a mile. Hamza spots that and leaves it alone. Buttler fails to collect it cleanly and the ball races to the fine leg fence. 100 up for the hosts.
Good length ball on middle, Malan works it to deep mid-wicket and calls Hmaza for a couple. The fielder comes across and cleans it up.
On a length on off, Malan camps back and blocks it out to the cover fielder.
NASTY! That is a snorker of a delivery from Ben Stokes! Short of a length ball around middle, Malan looks to sway away from it but gets hit around the chest area. He is fine though.
On off, pushed to point.
Good length ball on off, defended off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Malan flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single. Moves to 49.

FIFTY! That too on debut for Pieter Malan. This has been an excellent innings from Malan. He has not looked nervous at all in this innings and is going about his business comfortably. He gets there by working this full delivery down to long on for a single. Can he convert this to a debut ton as well?
Played through mid-wicket by the batsman. One run added to the total.
On off, Malan comes down the track and defends it out.
Floated on off, Malan strides forward and blocks it to short leg.

Flat one on middle, Hamza works it to deep square leg for a single.

Fuller one outside off, Malan psuhes it past the cover fielder and picks up a couple before the fielder hares after it and cleans it up.
Just short! Stokes digs in short outside off, Hamza hops and pushes it off the back foot towards cover. Broad dives in front but it falls short of him.
On a length on middle, Zubayr defends this one.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle, Hamza works it uncomfortably to the leg side and wants the single. Malan sends him back.
BOUNCER! Stokes bowls this one around middle and leg, Hamza looks to leave this but it hits him near the elbow and rolls to the keeper.
Another short one on off, Zubayr defends it out off the back foot.
Short of a length on off, Hamza rocks on his back foot and defends it out.
Root starts with a flighted ball on off, Malan defends it to cover.
Flatter one on middle, defended back to the bowler.
On off, blocked solidly by Malan.
OHH! Root dishes a floated ball down the leg side, Malan looks to sweep but it hits the gloves and goes above the hopping leg slip fielder. It goes towards fine leg and a couple is taken.
Flatter one on the pads, Malan tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Down the leg side again, Hamza lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball on middle, Malan defends it out.
Fullish on off, Malan pushes it towards deep point and wants a couple but Hamza sends him back. Only a single.
Short ball down the leg side, Hamza shoulders arms to it.

BEATEN! Stokes has to be more on this channel. Bowls it on a length in the channel of uncertainty, Hamza looks to push off the back foot but it whizzes past the bat and goes into the mitts of the keeper.
Short ball around middle and leg, Zubayr ducks under it.
Back of a length delivery on off, Hamza hops and defends it out.
Fuller one on middle, Malan defends it back to Root.
Malan drives this floated ball on middle past the diving bowler for a couple. The fielder comes across and cleans it up.
Flatter one on off, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, defended off the back foot.
Loopy delivery down the leg side, spinning down. Malan leaves it alone. Stokes dives to his right from leg gully and makes a good stop. Saved a certain four byes there.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Short ball outside off, Hamza sways away from it.
BOUNCER! It is bowled down the leg side, Hamza lets the ball go to the keeper.
Length ball on middle, Hamza defends it out to the leg side and single is taken.
Short ball outside off, left alone by Malan.
NO BALL! Stokes has overstepped again. Length ball on off, Malan pushes it through point and a single is taken. 50-run stand is also up between the two.
Short of a length on off, Hamza defends it out off the back foot.
Outside off, left alone by Zubayr Hamza.
Good start from Anderson. Length ball around off, moving into the batsman. Malan looks to leave but gets hit on the thigh pad. There was no appeal made from England. Looked a bit too high.
That was close! A good leave in the end. Full delivery outside off, nipping in a bit. Malan shoulders arms to it. The ball just whizzed past the off stump.
On a length on off, Malan strides forward and defends it to cover.
Outside off, left alone by Malan.
Full on middle, pushed back to Anderson.
Length ball on off, moving in a bit. Malan gets his bat down in time and defends it to the off side.
Curran starts with a full delivery on off, Hamza pushes it to deep cover for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Malan shoulders arms to this one.
Full on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball on off, Pieter taps it to gully.
Very full delivery outside off. It pitches and moves away. Malan leaves it alone.
Full delivery on off, Pieter is solid in defense and does so towards cover.
Length ball on off, Hamza blocks it off the back foot.

OUT! Caught behind! Hamza is out of here and all the pressure Anderson was building has turned into a reward. There is a hint of movement, the ball is doing something, who do you turn to? Without any doubts, James Anderson. He makes the ball move just like he has done in his previous 150 Test matches. It is in the corridor of uncertainty around off. It shapes in off the deck, Hamza has to defend it and has no option to leave it. The ball takes a thick outside edge and goes to the right of the keeper. Buttler dives and takes a good catch. The ball did not move leaps and bounds, it just did a fraction. Fraction enough to get rid of Hamza. The norm of this Test match has been late wickets in the day and that is exactly what has happened now as well.
Good length ball outside off, Maharaj leaves it alone.
Short delivery outside off, Keshav does not fiddle with it and lets it through to the keeper.
BEATEN! This is Anderson at his best! Brilliant bowling! Good length ball outside off, Maharaj looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length ball outside off, Maharaj leaves it alone. Excellent over comes to an end. A wicket-maiden it is.
Full delivery on off, pushed to cover for a single.
EDGY! Fullish delivery on off, Maharaj looks to defend off the front foot but goes off the outside edge through gully. The batters manage to take a couple. Maharaj is off the mark.
BEATEN! Beautiful delivery from Curran. Good length ball around off, Keshav attempts to defend but misses it altogether.
Very full delivery outside off, Maharaj looks to dig it out but fails to get any bat on it.
Length ball on off, Keshav defends it solidly.
Maharaj has managed to survive the last ball of the day as he defends this full delivery on middle back to the bowler. STUMPS ON DAY 4.
James starts right on the money. Good length ball pitching around off. It reverse swings a bit as it comes in. Malan is aware of his off pole and offers a very good leave.

Huge appeal as there was a noise as the ball went to the keeper. The English players are thinking for a review but opt against it. Excellent decision from both the umpire and Joe Root. Good length ball pitching around off, it nips back in sharply. Malan looks to defend but the ball goes between the bat and pad to the keeper. It clips something as there is a noise. There is a huge appeal as the English players go up in appeal but the umpire turns it down. Root thinks of a review and opts against it. Good decision as Ultra Edge later on shows that the noise was of the ball hitting the back pad on its way to the keeper.

First run of the day and it comes in the form of a leg bye. Good length ball pitching outside off. Malan once again fails to defend it off his bat. It goes to the off side off his thigh pad and they steal a leg bye.
Good length ball on off, Maharaj looks to defend but the ball goes off the outer half of his bat towards point.

Broken bat! Get a new bat please. Good length ball on off, it nips in. Maharaj looks to defend but does so off the upper half of his bat. The ball jars the bat and Keshav's bat is broken into two pieces. Proud moment for Jimmy. There is a certain joy a pace bowler gets breaking a bat. Anderson has done it at the young age of 37!
New bat comes in for Maharaj and he uses it to leave this length ball outside off alone.
Broad starts with a length ball, moving away. Malan lets the ball through to the keeper.
This time Broad dishes out a fullish delivery around off, Malan strides forward and guides it through point. The batters take two before the fielder comes across and cleans it up.
Length ball outside off, Pieter does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
On a length on middle, Pieter stands tall and blocks it to cover.
Fuller one outside off, Pieter lets the ball through to the keeper.
Malan lets another full delivery outside off go to the keeper.
Length ball outside off, Maharaj shoulders arms to it.
OHH! Fullish ball outside off, with some reverse but not enough to make Maharaj play as he leaves this one alone.
Outside off, Keshav makes a leave to the keeper.
Length ball outside off, Maharaj drives it but finds the mid off fielder.

OUT! LBW! England strike early and that is just what the doctor ordered. He was threatening towards the fag end of Day 4 and he has been threatening today morning also. This is another gem of a delivery from Anderson. One of the rare bowlers in modern day cricket who can generate good old reverse swing. Not as much as Wasim Akram used to do but enough to trouble the batter. This one starts around off. It looks to be shaping away but it comes back in. Maharaj looks to defend but misses and the ball hits him on the back pad. There is a huge appeal from the English players and the umpire is in agreement with them as he raises his finger. Keshav knows he is a candidate of plumb and with just one review remaining, the Proteas will not take the risk of using it with the nightwatchman. He starts walking back. South Africa need 309 more runs to win. England 7 wickets away from leveling the series.
Full delivery on off, Faf prods forward and defends his first ball to cover.
Fullish delivery outside off, Malan shoulders arms to this one.
On off, Pieter looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes through gully. Two taken.
Good length ball on off, Malan lunges forward and defends it out.
Full delivery on middle, Malan works it to mid-wicket where Crawley makes a half-stop and the ball rolls to mid on. Well fielded.
Length ball outside off, Pieter shoulders arms.
Length delivery outside off, moving away, Malan shoulders arms to it.
Good length delivery around off, Faf defends it back towards the bowler with a straight bat.
A good solid front foot defense from Faf now. Slightly fuller on off, du Plessis lunges froward and blocks it right off the meat of the bat.
Jimmy attacks the stumps, Faf defends it calmly.
Du Plessis is off the mark. Length ball on middle, Faf glances it through square leg for one.
Away from the off pole, Pieter leaves it alone.
This one comes in from outside off, Malan leaves it alone.
Full delivery on off, du Plessis solidly defends it to the off side.
FOUR! Nicely tucked away! Back of a length ball on middle and leg. Faf du Plessis works it down to the fine leg region for a boundary. The fielder comes across but the ball wins the race.
Length ball on off, Faf looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and rolls to point.
Short of a length on off, Faf rocks on his back foot and blocks it out onto the pitch.
Fuller one on off, du Plessis goes on his front foot and defends it to point.
Broad goes full outside off, Faf has no problems in leaving this one alone.

Another loud appeal but turned down. Good length ball around off, moving ina little. Malan takes a stride forward to defend but gets hit flush on the pads. Anderson and the rest appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Anderson has a discussion with Root for the review but decide against it. Good decision as it was umpire's call on impact and it was anyways missing the stumps.
On off, pushed towards cover for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Faf defends it solidly off the front foot.
On a length outside off, nipping in. Du Plessis shoulders arms to it.
Full delivery on middle, Faf defends it out.
Fullish outside off, Faf pushes it to cover and shouts a loud wait to his partner.
Length ball on middle and leg, Malan solidly defends it out.
Close! Very close! Length ball on off, Malan looks to defend but it takes the bottom edge and rolls just past the stumps.
Fullish on off, Pieter looks to push at it but the ball takes the inside half of his bat and goes towards square leg. Two taken.
On off, Malan blocks it off the front foot to cover.
Length ball on off, Malan takes his one hand of the handle of the bat and defends it towards point.
Good length ball outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
OHH! Anderson is making the ball tal out there. Full delivery outside off, with some reverse swing. Faf makes a good leave though.
Back of a length ball around off, with some extra bounce. Faf plays it well as he drops his wrists and defends it to gully.
Length ball outside off, Faf shoulders arms to it.
Fuller one outside off, moving in. Faf pushes it towards mid off.
Anderson dishes a length ball on off, Faf attempts to defend but it goes off the bottom edge and hits the boot. No run.
Fullish on off. There is some reverse swing on it. Faf does well to defend it to the leg side.
Stokes starts with a back of a length ball on middle, Malan works it to deep square leg for a single. Malan wants the couple but Faf sends him back.
Another one which is back of a length on middle, du Plessis tucks it to mid-wicket and crosses over for a single.
BEATEN! That's a beauty. Excellent. Fullish outside off, Malan looks to push but it just misses the outside edge and goes into the mitts of the keeper.
This time, Malan defends this length ball on middle back to the bowler.
On a length on off, Pieter defends it to gully.
Fullish ball on middle and leg, Malan works it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length on off, Faf goes on his back foot and defends it to cover.
Fuller one on middle, du Plessis defends it to the bowler.

Better throw and Faf would have been a goner! Good length ball on off, Faf looks to defend but it takes the inside half of the bat and goes towards backward square leg. They take off for a couple. Sam Curran comes after it quickly and throws it towards the keeper but it is a wild one. Had to throw it direct to the keeper. If he had done that, Faf would have been in trouble. Even his dive would not have saved him.
Full on middle, du Plessis pushes it to mid on.
Length ball outside off, Faf shoulders arms to this one.
That is a terrific delivery! Good length ball outside off, with some reverse swing on it. Faf shoulders arms and the ball just goes past the off stump.
Length ball on off, Malan defends it out to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Pieter lets it through to the keeper.
NO BALL! Stokes oversteps yet again. He digs in a short one around middle, Malan ducks under it.
On middle, worked to mid-wicket.
Good length ball on off, Malan defends it to cover off the front foot.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Malan stands tall and defends it out.
Length ball on off, Malan taps it to gully. He moves out of his crease which the gully fielder spots and then he throws it at the stumps but misses.
Bess starts with a flatter delivery on off, du Plessis whips it towards square leg and takes an easy couple.
Flat one on middle, du Plessis works it to short fine leg.
Looped up ball on middle, Faf goes on his front foot and defends it back to the bowler.

A loud shot but not given. Bess floats this one up around off, Faf looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball lobs off to short leg and then the England players put in an appeal for a catch. The umpire is unmoved. The visitors think of a review but decide against it.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Flatter one on middle, du Plessis works it to the leg side.
Stokes starts after the break with a length ball on off, Malan defends it to gully.
Fullish on off, Malan takes a giant stride forward and defends it to cover.
Length ball outside off, Pieter shoulders arms to this one.
NO BALL! Back of a length ball on off, Malan drops his wrists and defends it out to gully. Stokes has overstepped and the umpire signals it a no ball.
On a length on middle, Malan works it to deep square leg for a single.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around off and middle, du Plessis ducks under it.
Flatter one outside off, with some spin into the batsman. Malan lets it go to the keeper.
Flatter on middle, tucked to short leg.
Floated on middle, Malan defends it out to the off side.
On off, Pieter comes down the track and defends it out to the off side.
Floated on off and middle, defended solidly by PM.
Bess bowls a flat one outside off, Pieter shoulders arms.
Back of a length ball on middle, Faf hops and works it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on middle, du Plessis whips it to the leg side for nothing.
Stokes digs in a bouncer around off, Faf lets it go. Buttler hops and collects it. It is wided for height.
Fuller one on off, pushed to cover.
EDGY FOUR! Luck for Faf du Plessis! Short ball outside off, Faf looks to guide this but gets a thick outside edge which goes over the gully fielder and into the fence.

BEATEN! Nicely bowled! Length ball outside off, Faf looks to defend but it whizzes past his bat and into the mitts of the keeper. Buttler is interested and goes up for an appeal for caught behind but Stokes just walks back to his runup.
Full on off, guided to third man for a single.
Floated on off, Faf strokes it to mid on.
Flighted on off, du Plessis tickles it to short fine leg.
Floated on off, du Plessis pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, du Plessis prods forward and blocks it.
Slightly shorter on off, Faf glances it to square leg and shouts loud 'no, no, no' to his partner.
Floated outside off and it spins in. Faf looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Length ball on off, Malan defends it to the off side.
Full delivery on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball outside off, Malan shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball on middle, worked to mid-wicket for a run.
Outside off, left alone by Faf du Plessis.
FOUR! Well played from Faf du Plessis! Fullish outside off, du Plessis lunges forward and drives it through gully for a boundary.
Flatter one on off, Pieter defends it to point.
Floated on off, Malan stands tall and blocks it out.
FOUR! Excellent batting from Pieter Malan. Short of a length outside off, Malan goes on his front foot first but then rocks back and punches it through gully for a boundary.
The batsman dances down the track but decides to defend it.
Outside off, left alone by Malan.
On middle, Malan defends it back to the bowler.
Fullish outside off, du Plessis shoulders arms to it.
Fullish on off, defended to the off side for nothing.
Outside off, left alone.
Fullish on off, Faf taps it to the slip cordon.
Short of a length on off, du Plessis pushes it to cover.
Back of a length ball on off, Faf stands tall and then blocks it out.
Floated on middle, Malan comes down the track and pushes it down to mid on for a single.

OUT! Caught! What a moment for young Dominic Bess and England. Massive, massive wicket this for the visitors. This has come out of the blue. Against the run of play. The dangerous, the marathon man of South Africa, the Protea skipper, Faf du Plessis is out of here. Floated off spinner around off, Faf gets down on one knee and looks to sweep it with the spin. He hits it a bit uppishly and it goes straight towards Joe Denly at mid-wicket. He gets down to his right and takes a very good catch to get rid of the South African skipper. This could be the wicket England would have been craving for. The new ball is available in a short while and they have a new man out in the middle. The one thing Faf du Plessis would not have wanted was this, falling this way. England will once again have their tail up now. 274 runs more needed for the Proteas but England now 6 wickets away with 2 and almost a quarter of sessions still to play.
Full on off, van der Dussen pushes it to cover.
Flatter one on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Floated on off, Rassie drives it to short cover.
Length ball on middle and leg, Malan flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on the pads, Pieter whips it to mid-wicket.
Fullish delivery outside off, Pieter shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length delivery on off, Malan taps it towards point and a single is taken.
Full around off, Rassie plays a very good drive but the fielder at short cover dives to his right and makes a very good stop. Testing van der Dussen by keeping him at the striker's end.
Full on off, van der Dussen defends it.
Floated on off, Malan defends it out.
Ohh! Flighted ball outside off, Malan dances down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.

An apeal for LBW turned down! Flatter one around off, spinning into the batsman, Malan looks to leave it but gets hit on the thigh pad. Bess appeals for LBW but nothing from the umpire. The replays roll in and it shows that it was missing the off stump.
Tossed up on off, Malan taps it towards gully. The slip fielder makes a half-stop and the ball rolls towards point. Two taken.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, pushed to cover off the front foot.
Short delivery on middle, Rassie hops and defends it out.
Full on middle, van der Dussen defends it out onto the pitch.
On off, van der Dussen lunges forward and pushes it to point.
Back of a length ball on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Fullish outside off, Rassie shoulders arms to this one.
Very full delivery on off, Rassie defends it back to the bowler.
Curran starts with a loosener outside off, Malan has no problems in leaving this ball alone.
This time, Curran digs in a short ball on off, with some extra bounce. Malan stands tall and pushes it through covers for a couple.
Fullish ball outside off from Curran. Pieter shoulders arms to this one.
Fullish outside off, Pieter leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Malan makes another leave to the keeper.
Length ball outside off, Rassie leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball outside off, van der Dussen shoulders arms to this one.
Short of a length on middle, Rassie tucks it to mid-wicket and a single is taken.
On middle, Malan gets into position and defends it solidly onto the pitch.
Fullish delivery on off, Malan gets forward on his front foot and defends it to point.
On off, defended to cover off the front foot.
Fullish delivery outside off, Rassie shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball outside off, van der Dussen shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball on off, Rassie strides forward and defends it out.
Fullish outside off, Rassie does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
Comes over the wicket and bowls a length ball on off, van der Dussen solidly blocks it back to the bowler.

What a ball to end the session! Brilliant stuff from Curran! Back of a length ball around off, swinging in. Rassie van der Dussen looks to defend but misses. It goes off something to the keeper. Buttler dives to his right and takes a good catch. Sam is interested and appeals but the umpire is unmoved. Now then, the England players think of a review but decide against it. Right decision in the end as the Ultra Edge shows that there there was no bat and it had gone off the thigh pad. With that, it is LUNCH ON DAY 5.
Broad starts with a full delivery on off, Malan defends it solidly to cover.
Broad dishes a fuller one outside off, Malan lunges forward and lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball on middle, Pieter stands tall and blocks it out to the off side.
Another one which is full on middle, Pieter strides forward and defends it to silly mid on.
Broad bowls another full one outside off, Pieter makes another leave to the keeper.
On off, pushed to mid off and a quick single to end the first over after Lunch.
Fullish ball outside off, Malan shoulders arms to it.
Length ball on off, Malan defends it out to cover off the front foot.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Sam Curran. Good length ball around off, moving away. Malan looks to defend but misses it altogether.
On a length outside off, Malan leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Malan defends it out to the off side.
Curran goes full this time and it is outside off. Malan pushes it towards mid off.
Fullish on off, Rassie drives it to cover.
Back of a length ball on off, van der Dussen defends it to point off the back foot.
OUCH! Good length ball on off, swinging in.  Rassie van der Dussen looks to defend but gets hit on the body. No damage done though.
Length ball outside off, Rassie shoulders arms to this one.
Length ball outside off, keeping a little low. Van der Dussen lets it through to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Rassie works it to short leg.
Full delivery on off, Pieter Malan defends it to cover.
Good length ball on middle, Malan defends it back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone by Malan.
Fullish delivery outside off, Pieter shoulders arms to this one.

OUT! Caught! Massive wicket for England and a huge blow for South Africa! No maiden Test hundred for Malan but more importantly his marathon innings of 288 balls finally comes to an end. This is the wicket the visitors were craving for and they have finally got it. The ploy to give the new ball to Sam Curran has done the magic for Root. Curran comes over the wicket and hits the deck hard on off, it looks to be going away with the angle but this one straightens up after pitching and it also shoots a bit off the deck. Malan looks to defend but gets surprised by the bounce. He ends up getting a fat outside edge of his slant willow. It dies on its way to second slip. Ben Stokes standing there takes a very good catch, inches above the ground. The England players are up in celebration and Curran gets his first wicket of the innings and it is the big fish. South Africa have half their side back in the hut and the tourists are over the moon!
FOUR! Poor ball first up to Quinton de Kock. He is off the mark with an easy boundary. Slower full toss on middle, de Kock just whips it to the fine leg region for a boundary.
Fullish on off, Rassie pushes it to mid off.
Length ball outside off, van der Dussen shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball outside off, Rassie shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball on middle, van der Dussen works it to mid-wicket.

EDGY FOUR! Almost another wicket but it was not to be. Short of a length ball outside off, Rassie looks to pull it off the back foot but it takes the underedge and goes past the diving Buttler and into the fine leg fence.
Length ball on middle and leg, Rassie defends it to the leg side.
Fuller on middle and leg, de Kock defends it with a straight bat.
Length ball outside off, de Kock plays one of his favorite shot, the cut shot. But England have a man in the deep for protection so just a single.
Good length ball outside off, Rassie shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Rassie gets on his front foot and then defends it to cover.
FOUR! Just past Buttler! Short delivery down the leg side, Rassie looks to work it down the leg side but it goes off the gloves and just past Buttler. It races away to the fence.
On middle, defended off the back foot.
Good length ball on middle and leg, de Kock pushes it to mid on.
Fullish on middle, Quinton goes on his front foot and defends it out solidly.
On a length on off, with some extra bounce. Quinton looks to defend but it takes the inner half and goes towards square leg.
Fullish on middle, QdK works it to the leg side and an easy single is taken.

Good length delivery on off, Rassie prods forward and defends it out to cover.

Length ball on middle, Rassie blocks it out onto the pitch.
Fullish delivery on the fourth stump line, van der Dussen lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rassie defends it back to Curran.
Outside off, left alone by Rassie.
Full delivery around off,Quinton takes a big stride forward and defends it out.
Fuller one outside off, Quinton shoulders arms.
Full delivery outside off, de Kock pushes it back to Broad.
Length ball on middle and leg, de Kock defends it to mid on.
Full delivery on off, Quinton drives it to cover and makes a half stop. The ball rolls to mid off and a single is pinched.
Fuller one on off, defended out by Rassie back to the bowler.
Starts with a floated ball on middle, Quinton looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and just bounces in front of short leg.
Loopy delivery on off, pushed down to long on for a single.
Floated on off, pushed towards mid off for a quick single.
Fuller one outside off, Quinton pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter one on middle, worked to mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery outside off, driven towards mid off.
Full on middle, Rassie pushes it back to Bess.

On off, pushed to cover for nothing.
Loopy delivery outside off, spinning in. Rassie prods forward and then decides to leave it alone.
Loopy delivery on middle, Rassie defends it out onto the pitch.
Flatter delivery on middle, blocked back to the bowler off the back foot.

What happened there? Did Buttler miss a stumping? Very full delivery outside off, Quinton looks to drive but gets an inside edge, hits the pads of the keeper and rolls to short leg. The replays show that de Kock had moved his leg out of the crease a little. The short leg fielder tries to throw it back but misses. By that time, de Kock had got his leg back in. It would have been tough to call that a stumping chance as it was traveling quickly and Buttler found it difficult to get a hand on it as well.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flatter one on middle, de Kock defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, worked to the leg side.
Flat one outside off. de Kock guides it to third man.
On middle, blocked out onto the pitch.
Short around off, Rassie dabs it to the ground on the on side.
Floated off spinner outside off, van der Dussen lunges forward and pushes it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Rassie pushes it to cover.

Very close to the stumps and turning in sharply. Van der Dussen bends his back and defends it astutely.

Low full toss on middle, Quinton pushes it to mid on.
Flatter one down the leg side, Quinton leaves it alone.
OHH! Good keeping though. Floated one outside off, pitching on the rough, Quinton looks to cut but misses. Buttler collects it well.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
The batsman works it down the leg side.

Huge appeal for LBW! Turned down. Floated ball outside off, kept a little low and turned a little. Quinton looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. Denly and the rest appeal but not out given by the umpire. They think of a review but decide against it. Good decision as the replays show that it hit the inside edge and then went on to hit the pads.
Played to mid-wicket region by the batsman.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.

Loopy delivery on middle, defended out.
Nicely bowled! Floated ball outside off, pitching on the rough and causing it to spin. Quinton looks to flick but misses to get hit on the gloves and lobs wide of the short leg fielder. Lucky.
Pitches on the rough around the pads and spins in. Rassie leaves it alone.

Short on off, QdK goes on his back foot and keeps it out.

FOUR! Finally de Kock lets it loose. Tossed up outside off, it is slightly overpitched. De Kock decides that he is done with the blocking game and frees his arm to drive it through cover for a boundary.
Floated on off, van der Dussen defends it back to the bowler.
Floated delivery outside off, Rassie bends bends forward and then drives it through the cover region. The fielder hare after it andf clean it up before it reaches the ropes. Two taken.
Loopy delivery on middle, Rassie defends it out.
On middle, van der Dussen blocks it out.

Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

Short ball outside off, de Kock punches it off the back foot towards cover. Broad slides, but fails to stop the ball cleanly. It allows the batsman to take a single. 200 up for the hosts.
Floated ball down the leg side. Padded away.

Comes over the wicket and bowls a flighted ball around off, Rassie looks to pad it away but gets hit on the pads. An appeal is made for LBW but the umpire shakes his head. The England players think of the review but decide against it.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Floated on middle and leg, de Kock works it to the deep mid-wicket region for a couple. The fielder hares after it and collects it.
On off, defended out.
Loopy delivery outside off, de Kock looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and goes towards first slip. It bounces just in front of Stokes.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full delivery on off, pushed down to long off for a single.
Flatter one outside off, de Kock leaves it alone.
Floated on off, defended to cover off the front foot.

Well bowled! Flatter one outside off, pitching on the rough. It spins down and bounces a little more. Quinton looks to defend but gets hit on the gloves. It rolls to the off side.
On middle, defended back to the bowler.
Short ball outside off, de Kock punches it to deep cover for a single.

On middle, flicked to mid-wicket and a single is taken.
Wide outside off stump, the batsman leaves it alone.
Wow! A bouncer from a spinner! It is bowled around middle, Rassie pulls it to square leg.
On off, blocked solidly by Rassie.
Floated on off, bounced a little more. Rassie defends it out.
Full delivery on off, Quinton pushes it to cover.

Flatter one on off, pushed back to the bowler.

BOUNCER! It is bowled around off, Rassie sways away from it.
Length ball on middle, Rassie works it to deep square leg and an easy couple is taken by the batters.
Length ball outside off, Rassie shoulders arms to it.
Length ball on off, Rassie solidly defends it to the off side off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Rassie looks to flick but it goes off the leading edge and it goes to mid off.
Some spin there? Floated ball outside off, spinning away. De Kock looks to defend but misses it altogether.
Loopy on middle, worked to the leg side for a single.
Down the leg side, Rassie lets it go to the keeper.
Floated ball down the leg side, Rassie pads it away. There is a mild appeal for LBW but turned down by the umpire.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Flatter one on middle, pushed back to Root.
Good length ball around off, de Kock blocks it onto the pitch.
Shortish ball just outside off, de Kock waits and then taps it towards gully.
Effort ball from Stokes this one. 144 kph it is and a well directed one too. It is just outside off. De Kock sways away from it.
A couple! Short of a length ball outside off, this time de Kock taps it through backward point for a couple of runs.

Nicely bowled and well played too. Short of a length ball, bounced a little more than expected. Rassie hops and defends it out onto the pitch.
Short ball on middle, Rassie pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Full delivery on off, de Kock pushes it down to mid off and takes off for a run. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
Fullish outside off, Rassie leaves the ball alone.
Back of a length ball on off, Rassie pushes it to cover.
Flatter one on middle, de Kock defends it out.
Loopy delivery on off, defended off the front foot.
Floated on middle, worked to short mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Short ball outside off, pushed to cover.
Flatter one outside off, Quinton lets the ball go to the keeper.
BOUNCER! It is bowled around middle and leg, van der Dussen ducks under it.
Full delivery on middle, tucked towards mid on and crosses over for a single.
Short delivery outside off, Quinton lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish on off, pushed to cover off the front foot.
